1
00:00:00,492 --> 00:00:02,632
(It's a full-on spring day.)

2
00:00:03,002 --> 00:00:05,138
(Where are we that has sparkly waves hitting the shore?)

3
00:00:05,162 --> 00:00:06,531
This is Sapgyoho Lake.

4
00:00:06,532 --> 00:00:07,631
- You know every spot.
- Yes.

5
00:00:07,632 --> 00:00:09,101
I came here often to fish.

6
00:00:09,102 --> 00:00:11,202
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

7
00:00:11,402 --> 00:00:12,402
- Hello.
- Seon Ho!

8
00:00:12,403 --> 00:00:13,641
- Hello.
- Seon Ho.

9
00:00:13,642 --> 00:00:15,571
Why are you wearing a beanie on a shoot?

10
00:00:15,572 --> 00:00:16,712
- Seon Ho.
- Seon Ho.

11
00:00:16,842 --> 00:00:18,941
How many packets of noodles did you eat?

12
00:00:18,942 --> 00:00:20,051
- Gosh.
- You gained weight.

13
00:00:20,052 --> 00:00:22,011
You grew a beard. You're all grown up.

14
00:00:22,012 --> 00:00:23,552
Why did you age so much so suddenly?

15
00:00:24,322 --> 00:00:25,421
I can't do this.

16
00:00:25,422 --> 00:00:26,521
You can't do what?

17
00:00:26,522 --> 00:00:28,492
They're tearing into me before we even begin.

18
00:00:28,792 --> 00:00:29,961
Keep quiet, Seon Ho.

19
00:00:29,962 --> 00:00:31,521
- He's the director.
- Hello, sir.

20
00:00:31,522 --> 00:00:33,132
That's the main writer.

21
00:00:33,292 --> 00:00:34,961
Get on their good side. You can do it!

22
00:00:34,962 --> 00:00:35,962
Okay, fine.

23
00:00:35,963 --> 00:00:37,462
What's going on here?

24
00:00:37,832 --> 00:00:40,232
Seon Ho was rehearsing for his musical.

25
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:43,042
- He hurt his back.
- Oh, dear...

26
00:00:43,302 --> 00:00:45,401
It happened yesterday. Yesterday.

27
00:00:45,402 --> 00:00:47,172
- Suddenly...
- Our crew moved fast.

28
00:00:47,312 --> 00:00:50,642
However, a disaster was averted in just one hour.

29
00:00:50,742 --> 00:00:51,981
How so? There's a celebrity...

30
00:00:51,982 --> 00:00:53,462
who is free on Fridays and Saturdays.

31
00:00:54,452 --> 00:00:56,481
He can be cast on the day.

32
00:00:56,482 --> 00:00:57,721
We know such a celebrity.

33
00:00:57,722 --> 00:00:59,821
You can't put it like that.

34
00:00:59,822 --> 00:01:01,821
Who is that? It's our Kang Jae Jun!

35
00:01:01,822 --> 00:01:02,851
Hello, everyone.

36
00:01:02,852 --> 00:01:03,991
I'm the muscly pig, the wild boar,

37
00:01:03,992 --> 00:01:05,422
and Hyeon Jo's dad, Kang Jae Jun.

38
00:01:06,062 --> 00:01:08,131
- Hyeon Jo's dad.
- Actually, today,

39
00:01:08,132 --> 00:01:10,231
we'd planned to go on a family trip to Jeju Island.

40
00:01:10,232 --> 00:01:12,201
- Really?
- We canceled everything.

41
00:01:12,202 --> 00:01:14,131
- For real?
- The phone was on speaker...

42
00:01:14,132 --> 00:01:15,501
when my manager called.

43
00:01:15,502 --> 00:01:17,671
My wife Eun Hyeong said, "You must go."

44
00:01:17,672 --> 00:01:19,541
As soon as she heard it was 2 Days 1 Night.

45
00:01:19,542 --> 00:01:21,041
- You canceled your Jeju trip?
- Yes.

46
00:01:21,042 --> 00:01:22,812
Hyeon Jo's crying, though.

47
00:01:23,142 --> 00:01:24,511
He's wailing.

48
00:01:24,512 --> 00:01:25,911
Thanks for coming.

49
00:01:25,912 --> 00:01:27,811
We're grateful you came along.

50
00:01:27,812 --> 00:01:29,821
- It's a relief.
- Let's get things started.

51
00:01:29,822 --> 00:01:31,522
Today's destination.

52
00:01:32,582 --> 00:01:34,851
It's on the west coast where every spot is photo-worthy.

53
00:01:34,852 --> 00:01:36,391
(The sparkling sea on the west coast...)

54
00:01:36,392 --> 00:01:39,422
(and things to do in the beautiful nature)

55
00:01:39,522 --> 00:01:41,331
(Everywhere you go is a perfect backdrop.)

56
00:01:41,332 --> 00:01:44,012
It's a popular spring destination with many delicious foods to try.

57
00:01:44,162 --> 00:01:45,702
Dangjin, South Chungcheong Province.

58
00:01:45,902 --> 00:01:47,102
- Dangjin.
- Dangjin.

59
00:01:47,872 --> 00:01:49,552
We can get lethargic in the spring months,

60
00:01:49,702 --> 00:01:52,241
and we need to bring back the real variety mindset...

61
00:01:52,242 --> 00:01:53,442
that we've been lacking.

62
00:01:53,542 --> 00:01:55,212
When did we ever loosen up?

63
00:01:55,542 --> 00:01:57,311
(Strong pushback)

64
00:01:57,312 --> 00:01:59,112
Why do you pressure us so much?

65
00:01:59,342 --> 00:02:01,011
Who are you calling loose?

66
00:02:01,012 --> 00:02:02,182
We're not elastic bands!

67
00:02:02,482 --> 00:02:04,758
Let's go back. We can get lethargic in the spring months,

68
00:02:04,782 --> 00:02:06,821
and we need to bring back the real variety mindset...

69
00:02:06,822 --> 00:02:08,052
that we've been lacking.

70
00:02:08,492 --> 00:02:11,092
We prepared the Dangjin Tour of Passion.

71
00:02:11,662 --> 00:02:13,061
- It'll be tough.
- I'm afraid.

72
00:02:13,062 --> 00:02:14,192
We're done for.

73
00:02:14,392 --> 00:02:16,432
It's a competition between 2 teams of 3.

74
00:02:16,502 --> 00:02:17,531
- What?
- What?

75
00:02:17,532 --> 00:02:18,561
- We're just five.
- What?

76
00:02:18,562 --> 00:02:21,832
We invited someone very competent who will add...

77
00:02:22,202 --> 00:02:25,172
a scoop of passion to this trip.

78
00:02:25,302 --> 00:02:26,342
- What?
- Who's that?

79
00:02:28,872 --> 00:02:30,011
Are they here already?

80
00:02:30,012 --> 00:02:31,012
Come on out.

81
00:02:31,013 --> 00:02:32,041
- What's this?
- What's this?

82
00:02:32,042 --> 00:02:34,212
- Is it TVXQ?
- Someone's running toward us.

83
00:02:34,482 --> 00:02:36,052
(Who is it?)

84
00:02:38,122 --> 00:02:39,282
- What's this?
- What's this?

85
00:02:39,892 --> 00:02:40,992
U-Know time.

86
00:02:41,092 --> 00:02:43,222
Jae Jun, you're the special host!

87
00:02:47,132 --> 00:02:48,132
What is this?

88
00:02:48,962 --> 00:02:50,461
Jae Jun!

89
00:02:50,462 --> 00:02:52,001
(Moonwalking)

90
00:02:52,002 --> 00:02:53,171
Such passion.

91
00:02:53,172 --> 00:02:54,932
- Don't come this way!
- What is this?

92
00:02:55,302 --> 00:02:57,141
- Stay there.
- Hey.

93
00:02:57,142 --> 00:02:58,702
- Hey!
- Such passion.

94
00:02:59,472 --> 00:03:00,742
Show your passion!

95
00:03:01,342 --> 00:03:03,182
(I'm passionate too.)

96
00:03:03,482 --> 00:03:04,511
(That's enough.)

97
00:03:04,512 --> 00:03:05,512
What's wrong?

98
00:03:05,582 --> 00:03:07,512
(I got stopped before I even got started...)

99
00:03:07,682 --> 00:03:08,712
What's going on?

100
00:03:09,082 --> 00:03:10,082
Hey!

101
00:03:10,322 --> 00:03:12,522
(Is it really you, Yunho?)

102
00:03:13,492 --> 00:03:15,851
This is pure madness.

103
00:03:15,852 --> 00:03:17,792
- Yunho.
- Hey!

104
00:03:18,062 --> 00:03:19,831
Hello. Nice to meet you.

105
00:03:19,832 --> 00:03:21,161
- It's a pleasure.
- Yunho.

106
00:03:21,162 --> 00:03:22,362
(An extraordinary entrance)

107
00:03:22,732 --> 00:03:24,261
- Hello.
- I'm in shock.

108
00:03:24,262 --> 00:03:26,701
Hello. I'm here for the passion special.

109
00:03:26,702 --> 00:03:28,471
I'm TVXQ's U-Know Yunho. I'm in your care.

110
00:03:28,472 --> 00:03:30,072
(TVXQ's U-Know Yunho)

111
00:03:30,702 --> 00:03:32,172
(K-pop legend TVXQ)

112
00:03:32,372 --> 00:03:34,372
(Many of their records were idol firsts.)

113
00:03:34,972 --> 00:03:37,542
(First idol to sell out three-day concert in Nissan Stadium)

114
00:03:38,142 --> 00:03:40,051
(The only way to become perfect...)

115
00:03:40,052 --> 00:03:41,452
(is continuous practice.)

116
00:03:41,682 --> 00:03:42,981
("The most harmful insect to human is Lack of Effort.")

117
00:03:42,982 --> 00:03:44,358
("Your mentality rules your body.")

118
00:03:44,382 --> 00:03:46,851
(A living quote generator)

119
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:49,222
(U-Know Yunho, a man of passion)

120
00:03:49,592 --> 00:03:51,121
I had no clue whatsoever.

121
00:03:51,122 --> 00:03:52,792
You suddenly yelled at Jae Jun.

122
00:03:53,022 --> 00:03:54,391
What are you doing here?

123
00:03:54,392 --> 00:03:56,331
I got a call out of the blue.

124
00:03:56,332 --> 00:03:59,632
They said the 2 Days 1 Night members,

125
00:03:59,902 --> 00:04:01,602
compared to the early days...

126
00:04:02,632 --> 00:04:04,002
You spread that rumor?

127
00:04:04,072 --> 00:04:06,772
- What are you telling people?
- So...

128
00:04:07,012 --> 00:04:08,571
I got that call.

129
00:04:08,572 --> 00:04:10,812
- I'm closest to DinDin.
- Yes.

130
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:13,611
He is on multiple programs these days.

131
00:04:13,612 --> 00:04:14,711
He's more relaxed now.

132
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:16,111
He has loosened up totally.

133
00:04:16,112 --> 00:04:17,481
- It's serious.
- His YouTube is doing well,

134
00:04:17,482 --> 00:04:19,081
- so he completely...
- My mindset...

135
00:04:19,082 --> 00:04:21,021
was trashed from the start.

136
00:04:21,022 --> 00:04:23,891
I decided it would be a good chance to...

137
00:04:23,892 --> 00:04:25,532
- bring things back.
- Bring things back.

138
00:04:25,792 --> 00:04:27,031
It's a passion tour.

139
00:04:27,032 --> 00:04:28,292
- A passion tour.
- Yes.

140
00:04:28,462 --> 00:04:31,201
I'll make it so they do better.

141
00:04:31,202 --> 00:04:32,301
(I'll transform DinDin.)

142
00:04:32,302 --> 00:04:33,631
I like that. It's much needed.

143
00:04:33,632 --> 00:04:35,931
Sometimes, during a game, he sulks and shows his teeth...

144
00:04:35,932 --> 00:04:37,472
and whines, "I'm done."

145
00:04:37,672 --> 00:04:39,101
He did that before as well.

146
00:04:39,102 --> 00:04:41,341
- That's a pattern of his.
- How did you change him?

147
00:04:41,342 --> 00:04:42,612
By showing attention.

148
00:04:42,742 --> 00:04:44,141
- That's right!
- Be attentive.

149
00:04:44,142 --> 00:04:45,441
- How?
- That's so accurate.

150
00:04:45,442 --> 00:04:47,312
- Be attentive how?
- If you let him sulk,

151
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:49,451
- he walks about and grumbles.
- Yes!

152
00:04:49,452 --> 00:04:51,421
He grumbles to himself while looking at the waves.

153
00:04:51,422 --> 00:04:52,582
This is insane!

154
00:04:52,752 --> 00:04:54,591
He was always like this.

155
00:04:54,592 --> 00:04:56,721
- That's what he was like.
- After a while,

156
00:04:56,722 --> 00:04:58,021
- go up to him.
- And?

157
00:04:58,022 --> 00:04:59,621
"What's up? You can do this."

158
00:04:59,622 --> 00:05:00,831
"Yes, but..."

159
00:05:00,832 --> 00:05:02,061
Do that for a while...

160
00:05:02,062 --> 00:05:03,961
and he gives this halfhearted reaction.

161
00:05:03,962 --> 00:05:05,732
- "Okay."
- "I get it for now."

162
00:05:06,132 --> 00:05:07,731
If you just watch from a distance,

163
00:05:07,732 --> 00:05:09,202
he gets back into his groove.

164
00:05:09,702 --> 00:05:12,141
You just have to nudge him at the right time.

165
00:05:12,142 --> 00:05:14,211
Jong Min's wife.

166
00:05:14,212 --> 00:05:15,841
Her current love is Kim Jong Min,

167
00:05:15,842 --> 00:05:17,911
but her previous love was U-Know Yunho.

168
00:05:17,912 --> 00:05:19,381
- I heard that.
- Sorry.

169
00:05:19,382 --> 00:05:20,481
He sang at their wedding.

170
00:05:20,482 --> 00:05:22,081
She's a huge fan. Even now.

171
00:05:22,082 --> 00:05:24,052
- She still likes him?
- She gets butterflies.

172
00:05:24,552 --> 00:05:25,822
Thank you very much.

173
00:05:26,352 --> 00:05:28,751
Yunho took time out of his busy schedule.

174
00:05:28,752 --> 00:05:30,421
- He came from Japan.
- He went right back.

175
00:05:30,422 --> 00:05:32,292
He briefly flew in from Japan,

176
00:05:32,462 --> 00:05:34,331
- sang at our wedding, and returned.
- Yes.

177
00:05:34,332 --> 00:05:35,962
Did you get anything in return?

178
00:05:36,192 --> 00:05:37,331
- Nothing?
- Jong Min said...

179
00:05:37,332 --> 00:05:39,061
we should meet up in private later.

180
00:05:39,062 --> 00:05:41,101
We were both busy afterwards.

181
00:05:41,102 --> 00:05:42,701
- We were busy.
- That's not nice.

182
00:05:42,702 --> 00:05:43,841
He's too busy!

183
00:05:43,842 --> 00:05:45,641
If he were a little more considerate,

184
00:05:45,642 --> 00:05:46,741
- he'd have managed.
- Yes.

185
00:05:46,742 --> 00:05:48,412
You didn't do anything for him in return?

186
00:05:48,712 --> 00:05:50,982
He got TVXQ's U-Know Yunho to sing for free.

187
00:05:51,912 --> 00:05:53,142
I'll make it up to you today.

188
00:05:53,482 --> 00:05:54,751
- Today's the day.
- It's fine.

189
00:05:54,752 --> 00:05:56,551
It's okay. We talked on the phone, though.

190
00:05:56,552 --> 00:05:58,021
You have to pay him back for two days.

191
00:05:58,022 --> 00:05:59,082
- Right.
- Yes.

192
00:05:59,382 --> 00:06:02,821
By the way, Joon talked about TVXQ too.

193
00:06:02,822 --> 00:06:04,098
He said they were on another level.

194
00:06:04,122 --> 00:06:05,561
- Of course.
- Right.

195
00:06:05,562 --> 00:06:06,631
- They were on another level.
- We all knew.

196
00:06:06,632 --> 00:06:08,932
He said he couldn't even bring himself to look at them.

197
00:06:09,192 --> 00:06:11,031
Actually, I remember when MBLAQ made their debut.

198
00:06:11,032 --> 00:06:12,801
I was close to Rain.

199
00:06:12,802 --> 00:06:13,802
- Right.
- Yes.

200
00:06:13,803 --> 00:06:15,031
- Rain.
- He showed me...

201
00:06:15,032 --> 00:06:16,701
- their debut performance.
- I see.

202
00:06:16,702 --> 00:06:18,578
- Right. I remember that.
- You remember that, right?

203
00:06:18,602 --> 00:06:20,482
- He showed it to me.
- Have you worked with...

204
00:06:20,812 --> 00:06:21,971
- Jae Jun before?
- Jae Jun...

205
00:06:21,972 --> 00:06:24,211
looks like a local old man who came to the filming.

206
00:06:24,212 --> 00:06:25,241
All of a sudden...

207
00:06:25,242 --> 00:06:26,722
"My gosh, a lot of celebrities came."

208
00:06:26,782 --> 00:06:29,411
(He became visibly quiet after Yunho showed up.)

209
00:06:29,412 --> 00:06:30,421
(Reacting)

210
00:06:30,422 --> 00:06:31,922
(Glancing)

211
00:06:32,022 --> 00:06:34,391
(2 Days 1 Night is a tough one.)

212
00:06:34,392 --> 00:06:36,762
I thought there weren't any other guests.

213
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:38,291
- But there was.
- Improvising...

214
00:06:38,292 --> 00:06:40,061
Not just any guest, but a super famous one at that.

215
00:06:40,062 --> 00:06:42,232
- Why did they invite me then?
- My gosh, no.

216
00:06:42,392 --> 00:06:44,462
- He's flustered.
- You're the MC.

217
00:06:44,732 --> 00:06:46,932
I stutter, so I'm not even a good MC.

218
00:06:47,532 --> 00:06:49,371
- I'm a fan.
- My gosh.

219
00:06:49,372 --> 00:06:51,942
What percentage of your energy will you use today?

220
00:06:52,242 --> 00:06:53,441
Go easy on us. Come on.

221
00:06:53,442 --> 00:06:55,672
First of all, here's how I want to express it.

222
00:06:56,142 --> 00:06:57,541
I don't want to be the best one today.

223
00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:58,942
But I want to be the only one.

224
00:07:00,082 --> 00:07:02,312
- Your eyes are scary.
- Today won't be easy.

225
00:07:02,412 --> 00:07:04,151
Actually, that's also what I'm thinking.

226
00:07:04,152 --> 00:07:05,152
I see.

227
00:07:05,153 --> 00:07:06,651
- They're rivals today.
- Okay.

228
00:07:06,652 --> 00:07:07,791
(Holding tightly)

229
00:07:07,792 --> 00:07:08,821
- Let's do well today.
- My gosh.

230
00:07:08,822 --> 00:07:10,192
- How fascinating.
- By the way...

231
00:07:10,492 --> 00:07:12,692
Let us introduce a few more things.

232
00:07:12,922 --> 00:07:14,731
We're on Tour of Passion in Dangjin.

233
00:07:14,732 --> 00:07:17,632
U-Know Yunho, as the expert of passion,

234
00:07:17,732 --> 00:07:19,131
- has some famous sayings.
- There are a lot of them.

235
00:07:19,132 --> 00:07:20,331
So let's take a look at them.

236
00:07:20,332 --> 00:07:21,371
- There are so many.
- So many.

237
00:07:21,372 --> 00:07:22,931
- There are so many of them.
- Then we'll begin.

238
00:07:22,932 --> 00:07:23,941
It's that big?

239
00:07:23,942 --> 00:07:26,401
Today, we're trying to rekindle...

240
00:07:26,402 --> 00:07:28,141
- This is bad. Hold on.
- your passion.

241
00:07:28,142 --> 00:07:29,641
- My gosh.
- You know what?

242
00:07:29,642 --> 00:07:30,881
- He should...
- Him?

243
00:07:30,882 --> 00:07:32,211
- Jae Jun should read them.
- Me?

244
00:07:32,212 --> 00:07:33,511
- Yes, Jae Jun.
- Please read them for us.

245
00:07:33,512 --> 00:07:35,258
- I told you that I tend to stutter.
- Gosh, no.

246
00:07:35,282 --> 00:07:37,051
- Our director stutters a lot too.
- Okay.

247
00:07:37,052 --> 00:07:38,221
- He'll sympathize with you.
- Try to sound cool.

248
00:07:38,222 --> 00:07:39,682
- "Try to sound cool."
- It's okay.

249
00:07:39,922 --> 00:07:41,121
- Here it goes.
- Okay.

250
00:07:41,122 --> 00:07:43,091
- "One. Our mind rules our body."
- One.

251
00:07:43,092 --> 00:07:44,191
- It rules our body.
- Yes, that's right.

252
00:07:44,192 --> 00:07:45,192
- Our mind?
- Right.

253
00:07:45,193 --> 00:07:46,861
I think our mind is the most important thing.

254
00:07:46,862 --> 00:07:48,291
(Burning with passion)

255
00:07:48,292 --> 00:07:50,302
Your mind already rules your body.

256
00:07:50,602 --> 00:07:52,431
- It's already happening.
- My mind is already doing that.

257
00:07:52,432 --> 00:07:53,432
- Really?
- Yes.

258
00:07:53,433 --> 00:07:55,678
Rumor has it that you have no energy by the time you go home.

259
00:07:55,702 --> 00:07:57,442
Because I use up my energy at work.

260
00:07:58,172 --> 00:07:59,542
So you have no energy at home.

261
00:07:59,772 --> 00:08:01,071
Gosh, that's another famous saying.

262
00:08:01,072 --> 00:08:02,442
- I'm human too.
- I see.

263
00:08:02,742 --> 00:08:03,881
I'm not a robot.

264
00:08:03,882 --> 00:08:06,811
"Two. The most harmful insect to human is Lack of Effort."

265
00:08:06,812 --> 00:08:08,381
(The most harmful insect to human is Lack of Effort.)

266
00:08:08,382 --> 00:08:10,352
Where on earth did you say these things?

267
00:08:11,182 --> 00:08:14,192
Sometimes in life, it's necessary that we don't try so hard.

268
00:08:14,422 --> 00:08:18,062
But once we decide to do something, we must see it through.

269
00:08:18,722 --> 00:08:21,291
We shouldn't try to make excuses. We should just do it.

270
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:22,731
- That's a great saying.
- Right.

271
00:08:22,732 --> 00:08:23,831
- Three.
- Three.

272
00:08:23,832 --> 00:08:26,872
"There are three important things in life."

273
00:08:27,102 --> 00:08:28,871
(Cawing)

274
00:08:28,872 --> 00:08:29,971
(Let me pass through.)

275
00:08:29,972 --> 00:08:31,942
- That little bird...
- No.

276
00:08:32,102 --> 00:08:34,241
- You're doing a great job.
- What...

277
00:08:34,242 --> 00:08:35,741
- I just started talking.
- When Jae Jun was talking...

278
00:08:35,742 --> 00:08:37,582
The bird is giving its all too.

279
00:08:37,912 --> 00:08:40,352
- Hey. This is...
- The bird is working hard too.

280
00:08:40,482 --> 00:08:42,711
Jae Jun, let's go and bite off that seagull later.

281
00:08:42,712 --> 00:08:43,821
- Okay.
- Go ahead.

282
00:08:43,822 --> 00:08:46,552
"There are three important things in life."

283
00:08:46,682 --> 00:08:48,452
"Gold, salt, and now."

284
00:08:48,892 --> 00:08:49,892
Seriously.

285
00:08:49,893 --> 00:08:52,261
- What's this about?
- This one describes...

286
00:08:52,262 --> 00:08:54,332
my will to make today the best day,

287
00:08:54,592 --> 00:08:56,192
so I will be able to choose my tomorrow.

288
00:08:57,302 --> 00:08:58,732
I approve of this one.

289
00:08:58,962 --> 00:09:00,432
- Let's read the last one.
- Okay.

290
00:09:00,632 --> 00:09:02,071
"Stay in the cold water for three seconds."

291
00:09:02,072 --> 00:09:03,571
- The style...
- "You'll get used to it."

292
00:09:03,572 --> 00:09:04,772
"And that's life."

293
00:09:05,642 --> 00:09:06,941
Since you brought it up...

294
00:09:06,942 --> 00:09:08,388
On our show, we go into the water a lot.

295
00:09:08,412 --> 00:09:10,518
- Three seconds should do it.
- Do you think you can stay...

296
00:09:10,542 --> 00:09:11,758
in iced water for three seconds?

297
00:09:11,782 --> 00:09:13,751
I'm human too. So before going in,

298
00:09:13,752 --> 00:09:15,082
I might feel conflicted.

299
00:09:15,212 --> 00:09:16,711
But once I'm in there,

300
00:09:16,712 --> 00:09:19,451
I might be able to stay in for five seconds.

301
00:09:19,452 --> 00:09:20,591
- Really?
- Is that so?

302
00:09:20,592 --> 00:09:22,222
- Let me say this.
- Okay.

303
00:09:22,392 --> 00:09:24,291
Right now, you think he sounds...

304
00:09:24,292 --> 00:09:25,662
super energetic and cheerful.

305
00:09:25,862 --> 00:09:27,761
But once you spend some time with him, you get sick of him.

306
00:09:27,762 --> 00:09:28,931
(People get sick of him.)

307
00:09:28,932 --> 00:09:30,561
I bet by the time the night falls,

308
00:09:30,562 --> 00:09:32,331
you will tell him to stop it.

309
00:09:32,332 --> 00:09:34,052
- He'd still be energetic by then.
- Right.

310
00:09:34,472 --> 00:09:36,078
- He's just...
- His energy level will be the same.

311
00:09:36,102 --> 00:09:38,102
The Tour of Passion in Dangjin...

312
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,542
will be a 3-on-3 team match.

313
00:09:40,912 --> 00:09:42,641
Yunho and DinDin will team up.

314
00:09:42,642 --> 00:09:44,681
And Jae Jun and Se Yoon...

315
00:09:44,682 --> 00:09:45,841
- will team up too.
- Great.

316
00:09:45,842 --> 00:09:46,851
- That's good.
- I like that.

317
00:09:46,852 --> 00:09:47,852
Then these two remain.

318
00:09:47,853 --> 00:09:49,181
As for the last member,

319
00:09:49,182 --> 00:09:51,852
- why don't we let Yunho pick?
- He'll pick?

320
00:09:53,792 --> 00:09:55,521
- To be honest, - Yes.

321
00:09:55,522 --> 00:09:57,591
I don't know which team has the upper hand.

322
00:09:57,592 --> 00:09:59,168
- It looks like both of you...
- I don't know either.

323
00:09:59,192 --> 00:10:01,352
- Let's be honest.
- don't want to team up with Yunho.

324
00:10:02,162 --> 00:10:03,391
- Because...
- Actually...

325
00:10:03,392 --> 00:10:05,361
Because whoever joins our team won't be able to rest.

326
00:10:05,362 --> 00:10:07,601
- You can't rest then.
- My body has aged a lot.

327
00:10:07,602 --> 00:10:09,602
(My body has aged a lot.)

328
00:10:09,902 --> 00:10:11,601
It's been a while since anyone turned me down.

329
00:10:11,602 --> 00:10:13,602
It has the opposite effect. I want him on my team.

330
00:10:14,312 --> 00:10:16,112
He's so scary.

331
00:10:16,312 --> 00:10:17,942
People don't change.

332
00:10:18,712 --> 00:10:21,111
But depending on the company you keep around,

333
00:10:21,112 --> 00:10:22,681
you can blend in with them.

334
00:10:22,682 --> 00:10:25,351
- Today is the worst.
- Blend in?

335
00:10:25,352 --> 00:10:26,622
What's wrong with him?

336
00:10:26,892 --> 00:10:28,851
- Based on the company you keep, - That's true.

337
00:10:28,852 --> 00:10:30,792
- you could adjust the energy level.
- Right.

338
00:10:31,722 --> 00:10:32,792
So who will it be?

339
00:10:32,862 --> 00:10:34,631
Today, I'll pick Jong Min!

340
00:10:34,632 --> 00:10:36,131
(He picks Jong Min.)

341
00:10:36,132 --> 00:10:37,461
- What's wrong with you?
- Jong Min.

342
00:10:37,462 --> 00:10:39,601
Jong Min. He sang at your wedding.

343
00:10:39,602 --> 00:10:41,132
How could you be so rude?

344
00:10:41,202 --> 00:10:42,631
You're so mean.

345
00:10:42,632 --> 00:10:45,342
All right. Jae Jun, Se Yoon, and Joon will team up.

346
00:10:45,642 --> 00:10:49,671
Yunho, DinDin, and Jong Min will team up.

347
00:10:49,672 --> 00:10:50,681
Let's go.

348
00:10:50,682 --> 00:10:52,782
Jae Jun, scream for three seconds.

349
00:10:52,812 --> 00:10:54,382
(Shouting)

350
00:10:55,282 --> 00:10:56,282
Great.

351
00:10:56,752 --> 00:10:58,121
Save your voice.

352
00:10:58,122 --> 00:10:59,521
We're going to film all day.

353
00:10:59,522 --> 00:11:00,692
Let's follow our passion.

354
00:11:01,122 --> 00:11:03,122
All right. One, two, three.

355
00:11:03,452 --> 00:11:04,591
(Before going to the next spot)

356
00:11:04,592 --> 00:11:05,861
- Yes.
- Let's go.

357
00:11:05,862 --> 00:11:08,191
- That was a cool clap too.
- Gosh, no.

358
00:11:08,192 --> 00:11:10,202
- Thank you. We know it's early.
- Seriously.

359
00:11:10,302 --> 00:11:12,001
- It's nice to see you again.
- Seriously.

360
00:11:12,002 --> 00:11:14,301
So Joon moved into the dorm, and you lived on your own?

361
00:11:14,302 --> 00:11:16,831
I also lived in the dorm. But I had it to myself.

362
00:11:16,832 --> 00:11:17,841
- Really?
- Yes.

363
00:11:17,842 --> 00:11:20,171
Nissan Stadium is the biggest one.

364
00:11:20,172 --> 00:11:21,471
- It's the biggest one in Japan.
- Nissan Stadium?

365
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:22,811
- Really?
- Nissan as in the auto brand?

366
00:11:22,812 --> 00:11:24,711
- Yes.
- The Nissan Stadium...

367
00:11:24,712 --> 00:11:26,993
- can seat up to 75,000 people.
- There are 75,000 seats.

368
00:11:27,152 --> 00:11:28,511
- If the tickets are sold out.
- I see.

369
00:11:28,512 --> 00:11:30,498
It was our third time performing at Nissan Stadium.

370
00:11:30,522 --> 00:11:34,251
So we were lucky to have hit a new record.

371
00:11:34,252 --> 00:11:36,328
(His passion hasn't run dry even after a 22-year career.)

372
00:11:36,352 --> 00:11:38,992
I've never seen Yunho get tired.

373
00:11:39,092 --> 00:11:40,561
Let's follow our passion for now.

374
00:11:40,562 --> 00:11:41,831
(Looking forward to Yunho's performance)

375
00:11:41,832 --> 00:11:44,031
I thought even Gocheok Sky Dome was big.

376
00:11:44,032 --> 00:11:45,532
I was overwhelmed by the size.

377
00:11:45,762 --> 00:11:47,032
I see a chin-up bar.

378
00:11:48,032 --> 00:11:49,101
(A suspicious setup of a chip-up bar)

379
00:11:49,102 --> 00:11:50,102
- Gosh, this is...
- Something feels off.

380
00:11:50,103 --> 00:11:51,141
- It will test our passion.
- They set up...

381
00:11:51,142 --> 00:11:53,342
a solo stage for Yunho.

382
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:55,832
We're going to do chin-ups? I might easily beat them.

383
00:11:56,112 --> 00:11:57,741
(Joon is brimming with confidence.)

384
00:11:57,742 --> 00:11:59,712
- Let's go with our passion.
- My gosh, sure.

385
00:12:00,112 --> 00:12:01,681
We can just follow our passion.

386
00:12:01,682 --> 00:12:02,851
(Yunho seems relaxed.)

387
00:12:02,852 --> 00:12:06,082
Your lunch is at stake on your first mission.

388
00:12:06,522 --> 00:12:07,691
- My gosh.
- This is big.

389
00:12:07,692 --> 00:12:10,261
I heard his voice a lot on TV.

390
00:12:10,262 --> 00:12:11,392
- Really?
- Yes.

391
00:12:11,492 --> 00:12:14,591
So that's your real voice.

392
00:12:14,592 --> 00:12:16,131
(Pardon?)

393
00:12:16,132 --> 00:12:17,531
- What?
- "We'll begin."

394
00:12:17,532 --> 00:12:19,331
- What did you mean by that?
- I didn't mean it like that.

395
00:12:19,332 --> 00:12:21,532
- "We'll begin."
- No.

396
00:12:21,972 --> 00:12:24,241
I didn't mean it like that. He has a charming voice.

397
00:12:24,242 --> 00:12:25,722
- It's charming and memorable.
- Yes.

398
00:12:25,802 --> 00:12:27,611
Especially when he pronounces S...

399
00:12:27,612 --> 00:12:28,612
- You know him well.
- Yes.

400
00:12:28,613 --> 00:12:29,941
You should listen to him stutter too.

401
00:12:29,942 --> 00:12:31,041
My gosh. No.

402
00:12:31,042 --> 00:12:32,541
"U-Know Yunho is here."

403
00:12:32,542 --> 00:12:34,252
My gosh. No. He has a charming voice.

404
00:12:34,652 --> 00:12:36,311
- Here's your lunch menu.
- Listen.

405
00:12:36,312 --> 00:12:37,751
It's the symbol of passion...

406
00:12:37,752 --> 00:12:38,851
- See? "Symbol."
- and the source of power.

407
00:12:38,852 --> 00:12:39,852
- What is it?
- Wait.

408
00:12:39,853 --> 00:12:41,821
- Eels?
- It's eels with green onion kimchi.

409
00:12:41,822 --> 00:12:43,262
(Local eels with green onion kimchi)

410
00:12:43,792 --> 00:12:46,891
(To give you a boost of passion and energy when you're tired...)

411
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:48,961
- Eels with green onion kimchi.
- I love eels.

412
00:12:48,962 --> 00:12:51,231
- Eels with green onion kimchi?
- It comes with green onion kimchi.

413
00:12:51,232 --> 00:12:52,632
- That sounds tasty.
- With eels...

414
00:12:52,962 --> 00:12:53,971
- It's tasty.
- Yes.

415
00:12:53,972 --> 00:12:55,271
(He can't miss out on this dish.)

416
00:12:55,272 --> 00:12:57,472
I'm thinking of having a second child.

417
00:12:57,702 --> 00:12:59,701
- I must eat eels.
- You must eat no matter what.

418
00:12:59,702 --> 00:13:01,011
- No matter what.
- Yes.

419
00:13:01,012 --> 00:13:04,811
We've prepared missions that require your passion.

420
00:13:04,812 --> 00:13:06,912
- Gosh, we're in trouble.
- Today's Lunch Game is...

421
00:13:07,052 --> 00:13:08,982
Stamina Muscle Park.

422
00:13:09,112 --> 00:13:10,721
- Stamina Muscle Park?
- Stamina Muscle Park?

423
00:13:10,722 --> 00:13:11,782
Muscle Park?

424
00:13:12,052 --> 00:13:13,991
- They're super strong, though.
- Right.

425
00:13:13,992 --> 00:13:15,621
- Jae Jun is very strong too.
- Gosh.

426
00:13:15,622 --> 00:13:17,021
It's not about our power.

427
00:13:17,022 --> 00:13:18,991
- Can we even do one?
- It might not be about chin-ups.

428
00:13:18,992 --> 00:13:20,731
- You have Joon.
- Right.

429
00:13:20,732 --> 00:13:22,192
- Joon is very good at that.
- Yes.

430
00:13:22,592 --> 00:13:24,272
Joon is the problem. He might do over 100.

431
00:13:24,332 --> 00:13:26,301
- This is between you and Yunho.
- Right.

432
00:13:26,302 --> 00:13:27,772
You can't lose.

433
00:13:28,272 --> 00:13:29,471
But you never know, Se Yoon.

434
00:13:29,472 --> 00:13:32,142
Yunho does his dry rehearsal like it's the real thing.

435
00:13:32,242 --> 00:13:33,711
- Right.
- I'm serious.

436
00:13:33,712 --> 00:13:35,011
- Out of all the singers...
- He saw that.

437
00:13:35,012 --> 00:13:36,741
Out of all the singers I've watched perform,

438
00:13:36,742 --> 00:13:38,681
only TVXQ's rehearsals looked like the real performances.

439
00:13:38,682 --> 00:13:40,012
They always give it their all.

440
00:13:41,082 --> 00:13:42,511
(There are three important things in life.)

441
00:13:42,512 --> 00:13:44,021
(Gold, salt, and now)

442
00:13:44,022 --> 00:13:45,151
He's a senior singer now.

443
00:13:45,152 --> 00:13:46,381
Even his juniors don't do that.

444
00:13:46,382 --> 00:13:48,421
But this is what he does. I'm serious.

445
00:13:48,422 --> 00:13:50,391
From what I heard, after his passionate rehearsal,

446
00:13:50,392 --> 00:13:52,561
he would stand there and watch his juniors rehearse.

447
00:13:52,562 --> 00:13:53,861
- Right.
- He'd say things like...

448
00:13:53,862 --> 00:13:56,161
- "They're not giving their all."
- Right.

449
00:13:56,162 --> 00:13:58,262
But it's a new era now.

450
00:13:58,602 --> 00:14:00,831
- In front of them?
- I make compromises too.

451
00:14:00,832 --> 00:14:02,671
I make compromises to do half-hearted jobs.

452
00:14:02,672 --> 00:14:04,141
- Compromises for half-hearted jobs?
- Yes.

453
00:14:04,142 --> 00:14:05,702
- I make compromises too.
- My gosh.

454
00:14:05,902 --> 00:14:09,642
Everyone, there will be a total of three rounds.

455
00:14:09,942 --> 00:14:11,881
The team who wins two rounds...

456
00:14:11,882 --> 00:14:13,982
will get to have lunch.

457
00:14:14,712 --> 00:14:16,452
Round One of the Lunch Game is...

458
00:14:16,812 --> 00:14:18,722
Crossword Puzzle on the Chin-up Bar.

459
00:14:18,852 --> 00:14:19,921
- Crossword Puzzle?
- On the bar?

460
00:14:19,922 --> 00:14:21,292
- What's that?
- What is that?

461
00:14:21,392 --> 00:14:23,228
You're all familiar with crossword puzzles, right?

462
00:14:23,252 --> 00:14:24,391
- Crossword puzzles?
- I see.

463
00:14:24,392 --> 00:14:26,291
- We have to guess words, right?
- You write down the keywords...

464
00:14:26,292 --> 00:14:27,791
based on the number of boxes and the hints.

465
00:14:27,792 --> 00:14:29,291
(The first foreign film to sell ten million tickets in Korea)

466
00:14:29,292 --> 00:14:30,331
("Avatar")

467
00:14:30,332 --> 00:14:32,231
- Crossword puzzles.
- I see.

468
00:14:32,232 --> 00:14:33,332
- I know them.
- Yes.

469
00:14:33,432 --> 00:14:35,471
One of the members will have the hint cards...

470
00:14:35,472 --> 00:14:38,071
of the crossword puzzles on the bottoms of his shoes.

471
00:14:38,072 --> 00:14:39,741
(The hint cards will be on the bottoms of his shoes.)

472
00:14:39,742 --> 00:14:41,371
Then he will have to support himself on the chin-up bar.

473
00:14:41,372 --> 00:14:43,641
(He must raise his legs to show the cards.)

474
00:14:43,642 --> 00:14:45,811
- You'll have to do that, Joon.
- It has to be you, Joon.

475
00:14:45,812 --> 00:14:47,452
The other two members...

476
00:14:47,582 --> 00:14:49,411
must read the hints and guess the right keywords.

477
00:14:49,412 --> 00:14:51,582
Their goal is to complete the crossword puzzle.

478
00:14:51,652 --> 00:14:53,482
- I see.
- Then we have to be smart too.

479
00:14:53,922 --> 00:14:55,051
- Then...
- Right.

480
00:14:55,052 --> 00:14:56,852
- Yunho has to go on the bar.
- Of course.

481
00:14:57,722 --> 00:14:58,961
(They didn't even ask him.)

482
00:14:58,962 --> 00:15:01,692
We'll give you two minutes to complete the puzzle.

483
00:15:01,992 --> 00:15:03,462
The team answers...

484
00:15:03,732 --> 00:15:06,532
more questions within two minutes will win.

485
00:15:06,862 --> 00:15:08,602
You can put your feet down.

486
00:15:08,772 --> 00:15:10,471
But they can't touch the ground for more than two seconds.

487
00:15:10,472 --> 00:15:11,472
My gosh.

488
00:15:11,473 --> 00:15:13,193
- He won't lower his legs.
- Your thighs...

489
00:15:13,472 --> 00:15:14,811
- They'll be up in the air.
- Around my level...

490
00:15:14,812 --> 00:15:16,641
- He's the man of passion.
- Show us your passion.

491
00:15:16,642 --> 00:15:18,411
- He's the man of passion.
- Don't do that.

492
00:15:18,412 --> 00:15:19,441
(Feeling the pressure slightly)

493
00:15:19,442 --> 00:15:20,511
He's all about passion.

494
00:15:20,512 --> 00:15:22,228
- His feet won't touch the ground.
- For sure.

495
00:15:22,252 --> 00:15:24,382
I just want to say one thing to Yunho.

496
00:15:24,752 --> 00:15:26,552
Today will be a long day.

497
00:15:26,922 --> 00:15:27,922
So...

498
00:15:28,292 --> 00:15:29,621
- Don't worry.
- That's not important.

499
00:15:29,622 --> 00:15:31,368
The present moment is the most important thing in life.

500
00:15:31,392 --> 00:15:32,522
- What's going on?
- What?

501
00:15:32,622 --> 00:15:33,891
- Why do you look happy?
- What?

502
00:15:33,892 --> 00:15:35,831
- Why?
