1489
00:46:01,643 --> 00:46:03,813
what made you want to become a comedian?

1490
00:46:03,913 --> 00:46:06,483
- I majored in martial arts.
- Yes.

1491
00:46:06,583 --> 00:46:08,482
- But I got an office job later.
- What kind of job was it?

1492
00:46:08,483 --> 00:46:11,482
I worked as a salesman at a fabric company,

1493
00:46:11,483 --> 00:46:12,552
- You sold fabric?
- selling fabric.

1494
00:46:12,553 --> 00:46:14,322
I would have a meeting with designers.

1495
00:46:14,323 --> 00:46:16,853
One day, I was watching a comedy show.

1496
00:46:17,163 --> 00:46:19,322
I saw a recruitment ad for rookie comedians on the screen.

1497
00:46:19,323 --> 00:46:20,592
- You saw the recruitment ad?
- Yes.

1498
00:46:20,593 --> 00:46:24,002
While staring at the sky on the rooftop, I asked myself,

1499
00:46:24,003 --> 00:46:26,432
"Is this the life I really want?"

1500
00:46:26,433 --> 00:46:28,172
I don't know what gave me the guts, but I moved to Seoul...

1501
00:46:28,173 --> 00:46:29,632
- all by myself.
- You moved to Seoul.

1502
00:46:29,633 --> 00:46:31,542
- You didn't train to be a comedian?
- No.

1503
00:46:31,543 --> 00:46:33,072
- I went to the audition on my own.
- And you had no acting experience?

1504
00:46:33,073 --> 00:46:34,312
- Without even preparation?
- That's right. It's a true story.

1505
00:46:34,313 --> 00:46:35,719
- You passed the audition at once?
- I got hired at my first audition.

1506
00:46:35,743 --> 00:46:37,242
- Through an open audition?
- Yes.

1507
00:46:37,243 --> 00:46:38,489
(He got hired through an open audition at once.)

1508
00:46:38,513 --> 00:46:41,052
And then you met your wife.

1509
00:46:41,053 --> 00:46:42,282
My wife was my senior comedian.

1510
00:46:42,283 --> 00:46:43,389
(When Jae Jun was a rookie, Eun Hyeong was his senior.)

1511
00:46:43,413 --> 00:46:45,429
- They met each other...
- She is more competent than me too.

1512
00:46:45,453 --> 00:46:47,292
I'm glad I married her.

1513
00:46:47,293 --> 00:46:49,792
She's not just a great comedienne, but also a great person.

1514
00:46:49,793 --> 00:46:50,793
(My wife has a perfect personality as well.)

1515
00:46:50,794 --> 00:46:53,322
So I'm very happily married.

1516
00:46:53,323 --> 00:46:55,692
- That's great.
- You two seem so stable together.

1517
00:46:55,693 --> 00:46:56,832
- Thank you.
- That's right.

1518
00:46:56,833 --> 00:46:58,432
I think my wife is the one who keeps us grounded.

1519
00:46:58,433 --> 00:47:00,802
- And we take turns traveling alone, - Oh, right.

1520
00:47:00,803 --> 00:47:02,303
- which is cool.
- That's right.

1521
00:47:02,633 --> 00:47:03,672
(They arrived at the place where they'll have lunch!)

1522
00:47:03,673 --> 00:47:06,242
You visit many great restaurants while shooting 2 Days 1 Night, yes?

1523
00:47:06,243 --> 00:47:07,712
- We visit many great places.
- There are so many of them.

1524
00:47:07,713 --> 00:47:09,312
Do you ever go back to one of those places...

1525
00:47:09,313 --> 00:47:10,342
after the shoot?

1526
00:47:10,343 --> 00:47:11,483
I often do that.

1527
00:47:11,583 --> 00:47:13,012
There's another good thing about being on this show.

1528
00:47:13,013 --> 00:47:16,053
We always get to enjoy seasonal food.

1529
00:47:16,253 --> 00:47:18,153
Before I joined this show,

1530
00:47:18,683 --> 00:47:20,252
I didn't know much about seasonal food.

1531
00:47:20,253 --> 00:47:21,452
But now, when spring comes,

1532
00:47:21,453 --> 00:47:24,063
I crave food like webfoot octopus and flounder and mugwort soup.

1533
00:47:24,323 --> 00:47:26,539
They're tasty at this time of year. We always enjoy seasonal food.

1534
00:47:26,563 --> 00:47:28,609
I see some tables outside. I guess we'll eat outside.

1535
00:47:28,633 --> 00:47:29,753
I love the smell of the sea.

1536
00:47:29,963 --> 00:47:31,203
I can smell the sea.

1537
00:47:32,363 --> 00:47:33,602
- Look at this.
- Seriously.

1538
00:47:33,603 --> 00:47:35,079
(Today's lunch menu that makes them cheer)

1539
00:47:35,103 --> 00:47:37,502
- Let's all sit down.
- Look at this.

1540
00:47:37,503 --> 00:47:38,503
(Touched)

1541
00:47:38,504 --> 00:47:39,544
(Se Yoon smells the food.)

1542
00:47:40,973 --> 00:47:42,613
- Oh, my. Smell it.
- Oh, my.

1543
00:47:42,973 --> 00:47:44,533
- It looks amazing.
- I almost drooled.

1544
00:47:45,143 --> 00:47:47,812
What a nice blend of the aroma...

1545
00:47:47,813 --> 00:47:49,852
of the well-fermented kimchi and the eel.

1546
00:47:49,853 --> 00:47:51,659
(The eel's invigorating energy meets the nicely sour green onion kimchi.)

1547
00:47:51,683 --> 00:47:52,883
- That is...
- Smell it.

1548
00:47:52,953 --> 00:47:54,852
Spicy raw red stingray salad.

1549
00:47:54,853 --> 00:47:56,013
- I almost drooled.
- Oh, my.

1550
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:57,392
- It looks so amazing.
- Indeed.

1551
00:47:57,393 --> 00:47:58,692
It must go perfectly well with rice.

1552
00:47:58,693 --> 00:47:59,863
(It smells like paradise.)

1553
00:48:00,993 --> 00:48:02,193
Hey, go away.

1554
00:48:02,293 --> 00:48:04,533
- What's that? Is it eel?
- Let me just smell it.

1555
00:48:05,933 --> 00:48:06,962
(The appearance alone is already so incredible.)

1556
00:48:06,963 --> 00:48:08,802
- Go away.
- Green onions enhance...

1557
00:48:08,803 --> 00:48:12,243
the absorption of nutrients from conger eel...

1558
00:48:12,443 --> 00:48:15,112
and maximize fatigue recovery.

1559
00:48:15,113 --> 00:48:16,712
So, I guess we really are...

1560
00:48:16,713 --> 00:48:17,782
eating these dishes without them.

1561
00:48:17,783 --> 00:48:19,642
- Of course.
- We don't have to give them any.

1562
00:48:19,643 --> 00:48:21,512
- We're not even sorry to them.
- That's right.

1563
00:48:21,513 --> 00:48:23,233
They would be just like us if they had won.

1564
00:48:23,283 --> 00:48:24,422
- I'm hungry.
- This is really...

1565
00:48:24,423 --> 00:48:25,583
I'm starving.

1566
00:48:25,853 --> 00:48:28,022
- Gosh, those dishes...
- Thank you for the food.

1567
00:48:28,023 --> 00:48:29,529
- We'll enjoy the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1568
00:48:29,553 --> 00:48:30,623
Let's enjoy the food.

1569
00:48:30,793 --> 00:48:31,923
I'll try a piece.

1570
00:48:31,993 --> 00:48:34,133
(He puts a big piece in his mouth.)

1571
00:48:34,193 --> 00:48:35,193
Oh, my. Look at that.

1572
00:48:35,194 --> 00:48:36,763
(Curious)

1573
00:48:37,263 --> 00:48:38,833
First of all, I like the texture.

1574
00:48:39,163 --> 00:48:41,733
The eel became tender.

1575
00:48:42,203 --> 00:48:44,903
And it's spicy. I mean, the eel...

1576
00:48:45,103 --> 00:48:46,772
The eel has soaked up the spicy broth.

1577
00:48:46,773 --> 00:48:47,773
(It's bursting with the piquant and spicy flavor of green onion kimchi.)

1578
00:48:47,774 --> 00:48:49,842
- The eel has soaked up the broth.
- It's slightly firmer...

1579
00:48:49,843 --> 00:48:51,003
than the loach in loach soup.

1580
00:48:51,183 --> 00:48:52,183
- Really?
- Yes.

1581
00:48:52,184 --> 00:48:55,653
- Oh, I can feel that.
- The green onion kimchi is so good.

1582
00:48:56,483 --> 00:48:58,423
You know how pleasantly sour it can be, right?

1583
00:48:58,483 --> 00:49:00,523
- Of course.
- It's also sweet at the same time.

1584
00:49:01,253 --> 00:49:02,733
It's sour and sweet at the same time.

1585
00:49:03,393 --> 00:49:05,923
- The green onion kimchi is so good.
- It's hard to imagine.

1586
00:49:06,363 --> 00:49:08,163
(Peeping)

1587
00:49:10,033 --> 00:49:12,533
- Gosh. I thought you'd hit me.
- Be careful. He bites.

1588
00:49:12,833 --> 00:49:13,833
He bites.

1589
00:49:14,633 --> 00:49:16,732
Even though you lost,

1590
00:49:16,733 --> 00:49:18,702
- you need to eat something.
- Right.

1591
00:49:18,703 --> 00:49:20,472
- We'll give you food now.
- Really?

1592
00:49:20,473 --> 00:49:22,172
Can't we have at least the green onion kimchi...

1593
00:49:22,173 --> 00:49:23,373
- in the stew?
- Right.

1594
00:49:23,943 --> 00:49:24,982
No way. Try again.

1595
00:49:24,983 --> 00:49:25,983
(Stop what you're doing.)

1596
00:49:25,983 --> 00:49:26,983
Try again.

1597
00:49:26,983 --> 00:49:27,983
(They only get rice and regular kimchi.)

1598
00:49:27,984 --> 00:49:29,082
Bring us something else.

1599
00:49:29,083 --> 00:49:30,682
Give us green onion kimchi too!

1600
00:49:30,683 --> 00:49:31,929
(Give us green onion kimchi too!)

1601
00:49:31,953 --> 00:49:33,023
This is okay.

1602
00:49:33,183 --> 00:49:34,852
I mean, it's still...

1603
00:49:34,853 --> 00:49:37,092
Can't we have some meat?

1604
00:49:37,093 --> 00:49:38,922
We should be grateful. We have rice.

1605
00:49:38,923 --> 00:49:39,923
(Losers don't get meat.)

1606
00:49:40,763 --> 00:49:41,933
This is still good.

1607
00:49:42,063 --> 00:49:43,163
Cheer up.

1608
00:49:43,333 --> 00:49:45,102
We shouldn't be...

1609
00:49:45,103 --> 00:49:47,132
- discouraged already.
- Right.

1610
00:49:47,133 --> 00:49:48,432
Let's just eat what we have.

1611
00:49:48,433 --> 00:49:49,902
(I'm relieved that we get to eat, at least.)

1612
00:49:49,903 --> 00:49:51,172
We didn't get a real meal...

1613
00:49:51,173 --> 00:49:52,173
(Let's eat for now.)

1614
00:49:52,174 --> 00:49:53,373
after all that hard work.

1615
00:49:54,273 --> 00:49:55,273
But...

1616
00:49:56,573 --> 00:49:57,612
this kimchi is good.

1617
00:49:57,613 --> 00:49:58,613
(Unlike what he says, he's choked with emotion.)

1618
00:49:58,614 --> 00:49:59,694
Gosh. I can't believe this.

1619
00:50:00,113 --> 00:50:01,553
- Darn.
- The kimchi is good, right?

1620
00:50:01,913 --> 00:50:03,353
(Nodding absently)

1621
00:50:03,713 --> 00:50:04,722
Gosh.

1622
00:50:04,723 --> 00:50:06,323
(He's eating absent-mindedly.)

1623
00:50:06,423 --> 00:50:08,623
I love the crunchy texture of this.

1624
00:50:09,193 --> 00:50:11,062
Red stingray has a fun texture.

1625
00:50:11,063 --> 00:50:12,693
- It's enjoyable to chew it.
- Indeed.

1626
00:50:12,823 --> 00:50:14,532
- It's crunchy.
- That must be good.

1627
00:50:14,533 --> 00:50:15,863
- It's good.
- To be honest,

1628
00:50:16,093 --> 00:50:18,502
this dish has a unique texture thanks to the red stingray,

1629
00:50:18,503 --> 00:50:20,332
but the flavor is familiar to us. On the other hand, this one is...

1630
00:50:20,333 --> 00:50:21,433
(Gulping down the food)

1631
00:50:21,773 --> 00:50:23,533
This stew is something else.

1632
00:50:23,673 --> 00:50:25,572
They make an amazing combination.

1633
00:50:25,573 --> 00:50:26,573
Exactly.

1634
00:50:27,443 --> 00:50:29,273
(Trying to talk to him secretly)

1635
00:50:29,913 --> 00:50:31,843
(Tapping desperately)

1636
00:50:32,183 --> 00:50:33,989
- Leave me alone. Stop tapping.
- Give me just a little bit.

1637
00:50:34,013 --> 00:50:35,483
I'm not giving you anything.

1638
00:50:36,053 --> 00:50:37,182
Would you agree...

1639
00:50:37,183 --> 00:50:39,052
to let them earn a bite of your food...

1640
00:50:39,053 --> 00:50:40,382
through a game?

1641
00:50:40,383 --> 00:50:41,652
Oh, yes. Of course.

1642
00:50:41,653 --> 00:50:43,292
- Do you have more than enough food?
- What shall we do?

1643
00:50:43,293 --> 00:50:44,293
What...

1644
00:50:44,294 --> 00:50:45,522
(Hopeful)

1645
00:50:45,523 --> 00:50:47,992
We'll just eat at our normal pace.

1646
00:50:47,993 --> 00:50:49,332
Sounds great.

1647
00:50:49,333 --> 00:50:51,093
They have to hurry if they want to eat some.

1648
00:50:51,133 --> 00:50:53,632
Then let's play a quick game...

1649
00:50:53,633 --> 00:50:55,273
using rice bowls.

1650
00:50:55,733 --> 00:50:58,772
The first person to flip all three bowls on a tray...

1651
00:50:58,773 --> 00:51:00,502
will have a bite of the eel dish.

1652
00:51:00,503 --> 00:51:02,543
(The 1st person to flip 3 bowls will get the food.)

1653
00:51:02,613 --> 00:51:04,212
Okay. No practicing.

1654
00:51:04,213 --> 00:51:05,312
- Let's play rock-paper-scissors.
- Decide the order first.

1655
00:51:05,313 --> 00:51:06,789
Will it be over if I succeed in my first attempt?

1656
00:51:06,813 --> 00:51:07,959
- That's correct.
- It will be over.

1657
00:51:07,983 --> 00:51:09,689
- Let's do this.
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

1658
00:51:09,713 --> 00:51:11,083
Rock-paper-scissors. Again.

1659
00:51:11,423 --> 00:51:12,623
- Okay.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

1660
00:51:12,753 --> 00:51:13,753
The 1st, 2nd, and 3rd.

1661
00:51:14,053 --> 00:51:15,053
Here we go.

1662
00:51:15,054 --> 00:51:16,093
(Se Yoon will try.)

1663
00:51:17,893 --> 00:51:19,923
Gosh. Seriously.

1664
00:51:20,793 --> 00:51:23,833
(Se Yoon succeeds on his first try.)

1665
00:51:23,893 --> 00:51:25,762
- What is this?
- What?

1666
00:51:25,763 --> 00:51:27,003
I can't believe this.

1667
00:51:28,033 --> 00:51:29,909
- Did you succeed on your first try?
- I need to hurry up.

1668
00:51:29,933 --> 00:51:32,273
(He sits at the table without even looking back.)

1669
00:51:32,503 --> 00:51:33,572
What is up with him?

1670
00:51:33,573 --> 00:51:34,612
Just a little bit.

1671
00:51:34,613 --> 00:51:37,173
(The game ended quickly, and they lost their chance to eat.)

1672
00:51:37,883 --> 00:51:39,383
- Is it easy?
- If you...

1673
00:51:39,483 --> 00:51:42,153
try and succeed, we'll give you a small dish.

1674
00:51:42,183 --> 00:51:43,513
Okay. I'll try.

1675
00:51:44,483 --> 00:51:46,083
We'll give you a small dish.

1676
00:51:46,453 --> 00:51:48,413
(The game restarts in the midst of indifference.)

1677
00:51:49,823 --> 00:51:51,592
- Oh, it's difficult.
- Give me a chance too.

1678
00:51:51,593 --> 00:51:54,162
- Okay. If you succeed in one go...
- Yes. I'll try too.

1679
00:51:54,163 --> 00:51:56,193
He's good at everything that's related to food.

1680
00:51:56,433 --> 00:51:57,563
Those are rice bowls.

1681
00:51:57,963 --> 00:51:59,733
- How does he do that?
- I'll start.

1682
00:51:59,833 --> 00:52:01,953
We'll give you a small dish if you succeed in one go.

1683
00:52:03,103 --> 00:52:04,303
I made it.

1684
00:52:06,073 --> 00:52:08,343
(Jae Jun succeeds in one go too.)

1685
00:52:08,473 --> 00:52:10,513
(Only Joon failed.)

1686
00:52:11,283 --> 00:52:12,582
(Jae Jun gains a small dish.)

1687
00:52:12,583 --> 00:52:13,783
I'm tearing up.

1688
00:52:13,943 --> 00:52:16,113
- I made it.
- Hurry up and go, Jae Jun.

1689
00:52:16,753 --> 00:52:18,993
- I'll give it to you. Gosh.
- No, give me only the eel.

1690
00:52:19,683 --> 00:52:20,952
What's interesting is...

1691
00:52:20,953 --> 00:52:23,513
that he's taking both of the dishes. He knows how to enjoy food.

1692
00:52:23,753 --> 00:52:25,599
Hey, what are you doing? Why are you taking so much?

1693
00:52:25,623 --> 00:52:27,463
Wait. Hey, stop. My gosh.

1694
00:52:27,593 --> 00:52:28,892
- My goodness.
- Hold on.

1695
00:52:28,893 --> 00:52:30,363
- You can't...
- That's a lot.

1696
00:52:30,703 --> 00:52:31,903
Look at that.

1697
00:52:32,663 --> 00:52:34,302
(He piled up the food as high as possible.)

1698
00:52:34,303 --> 00:52:36,279
What happens if he drops some of it on his way back?

1699
00:52:36,303 --> 00:52:38,742
- You can only take what's allowed.
- You shouldn't do that.

1700
00:52:38,743 --> 00:52:40,712
- What?
- Gosh. What is that?

1701
00:52:40,713 --> 00:52:41,842
(The small dish is heaped with food.)

1702
00:52:41,843 --> 00:52:42,843
This is great.

1703
00:52:42,844 --> 00:52:43,872
- I feel the happiest I've been...
- Dig in.

1704
00:52:43,873 --> 00:52:45,142
Since the shoot began.

1705
00:52:45,143 --> 00:52:46,143
(He looks like the happiest man in the world.)

1706
00:52:46,144 --> 00:52:47,483
Eat up now.

1707
00:52:47,583 --> 00:52:49,353
The spicy raw red stingray salad is good.

1708
00:52:49,613 --> 00:52:51,983
This spicy raw red stingray salad is amazing.

1709
00:52:52,153 --> 00:52:55,193
The vegetables in the salad are the real kick.

1710
00:52:57,523 --> 00:52:58,523
(This is what happiness feels like.)

1711
00:52:58,524 --> 00:52:59,563
How does it taste?

1712
00:52:59,593 --> 00:53:01,962
The spicy raw red stingray salad does have a nice texture.

1713
00:53:01,963 --> 00:53:04,032
- It's crunchy, right?
- It's crunchy...

1714
00:53:04,033 --> 00:53:06,033
- and well-seasoned.
- Yes, it's well-seasoned.

1715
00:53:06,333 --> 00:53:09,103
The spicy raw red stingray salad is so good. Nice.

1716
00:53:09,803 --> 00:53:11,043
It's so good. My goodness.

1717
00:53:11,773 --> 00:53:13,172
It's so nice to eat food...

1718
00:53:13,173 --> 00:53:14,412
while looking at the sea.

1719
00:53:14,413 --> 00:53:17,243
With Yunho here, this seems like a scene from "Low Life."

1720
00:53:17,783 --> 00:53:19,182
This place looks like the filming location of the drama.

1721
00:53:19,183 --> 00:53:20,242
(The scenery has a similar vibe to the drama.)

1722
00:53:20,243 --> 00:53:21,552
Was it CGI or did you actually make that face?

1723
00:53:21,553 --> 00:53:22,782
- It wasn't CGI.
- Did you make that face?

1724
00:53:22,783 --> 00:53:23,982
Yes, I made that face. I mean...

1725
00:53:23,983 --> 00:53:25,459
The scene where my eyes rolled back, right?

1726
00:53:25,483 --> 00:53:26,582
(- What a perfect role for him.
- He stands out as an actor now.)

1727
00:53:26,583 --> 00:53:28,569
(It seemed so realistic when his eyes rolled back.)

1728
00:53:28,593 --> 00:53:31,493
(The viewers raved about his performance in this scene.)

1729
00:53:31,863 --> 00:53:33,262
(It wasn't CGI. He actually made that face.)

1730
00:53:33,263 --> 00:53:34,832
Can you reenact the scene...

1731
00:53:34,833 --> 00:53:35,962
after having a bite of green onion kimchi?

