2373
01:14:56,311 --> 01:14:57,640
- Jae Jun.
- Okay.

2374
01:14:57,641 --> 01:14:59,357
Why do you look so exhausted after one match?

2375
01:14:59,381 --> 01:15:01,511
Take a breather. Let's start with Joon.

2376
01:15:01,611 --> 01:15:02,987
(This time, Joon will start for Team Jae Jun.)

2377
01:15:03,011 --> 01:15:05,781
Shout out, "Come out, Yunho!"

2378
01:15:05,821 --> 01:15:08,390
But...

2379
01:15:08,391 --> 01:15:10,067
You have to break free from this. How long will you be like this?

2380
01:15:10,091 --> 01:15:11,390
He's a difficult person to me.

2381
01:15:11,391 --> 01:15:14,060
He may be difficult, but there's no seniority in competition.

2382
01:15:14,061 --> 01:15:16,791
- Yunho is too much for me.
- Go!

2383
01:15:17,631 --> 01:15:19,600
Can someone else come out first?

2384
01:15:19,601 --> 01:15:21,731
- I won't go.
- Same here.

2385
01:15:22,471 --> 01:15:24,100
- Fall off on your own, then.
- Hold on.

2386
01:15:24,101 --> 01:15:25,200
- This is too hard for me.
- Go for it.

2387
01:15:25,201 --> 01:15:26,540
This is too painful.

2388
01:15:26,541 --> 01:15:27,571
Get ready!

2389
01:15:28,341 --> 01:15:31,711
(The second match begins.)

2390
01:15:32,011 --> 01:15:34,911
(Yunho rushes toward Joon right away.)

2391
01:15:36,251 --> 01:15:37,251
Gosh. Hold him.

2392
01:15:37,252 --> 01:15:38,480
(Joon fights back.)

2393
01:15:38,481 --> 01:15:39,580
We'll hold you.

2394
01:15:39,581 --> 01:15:40,820
(Unlike his worries, )

2395
01:15:40,821 --> 01:15:43,091
(he fights on his own on the opponent's side.)

2396
01:15:43,491 --> 01:15:45,891
(Team Yunho blocks Joon together.)

2397
01:15:46,821 --> 01:15:47,821
We got him!

2398
01:15:48,831 --> 01:15:51,961
(Joon falls in the end!)

2399
01:15:52,001 --> 01:15:54,501
- We got him!
- Push him off!

2400
01:15:57,101 --> 01:16:00,771
(One person feels frustrated by all of this.)

2401
01:16:01,841 --> 01:16:03,041
My gosh!

2402
01:16:03,241 --> 01:16:05,381
(The closer appears.)

2403
01:16:06,111 --> 01:16:09,251
(Falling like autumn leaves)

2404
01:16:09,381 --> 01:16:11,941
(Jong Min and DinDin get eliminated as soon as Jae Jun appears.)

2405
01:16:12,021 --> 01:16:13,151
(Laughing)

2406
01:16:14,351 --> 01:16:16,150
(Jae Jun and Yunho go against each other again.)

2407
01:16:16,151 --> 01:16:17,190
Watch out!

2408
01:16:17,191 --> 01:16:20,791
(Will Yunho be able to fight back this time?)

2409
01:16:21,591 --> 01:16:22,831
It's Yunho!

2410
01:16:24,361 --> 01:16:25,830
- Yes!
- Jae Jun!

2411
01:16:25,831 --> 01:16:27,531
- Gosh!
- We don't stand a chance.

2412
01:16:27,631 --> 01:16:30,831
(Team Jae Jun takes Round 1.)

2413
01:16:31,371 --> 01:16:33,371
(Plopping down)

2414
01:16:33,641 --> 01:16:35,810
Breathe.

2415
01:16:35,811 --> 01:16:37,111
We don't stand a chance.

2416
01:16:37,511 --> 01:16:38,991
Gosh, we really don't stand a chance.

2417
01:16:39,281 --> 01:16:41,381
For Round One, the Bull Fight,

2418
01:16:41,781 --> 01:16:43,210
Team Jae Jun takes the win.

2419
01:16:43,211 --> 01:16:44,710
(Another win and they can be free from entering the water.)

2420
01:16:44,711 --> 01:16:46,751
- Do you know what's interesting?
- What is it?

2421
01:16:46,951 --> 01:16:48,921
Even for the first game,

2422
01:16:49,121 --> 01:16:50,690
we were losing at the start.

2423
01:16:50,691 --> 01:16:52,361
- Was that so?
- Right.

2424
01:16:53,591 --> 01:16:55,061
Did someone tear you up?

2425
01:16:55,431 --> 01:16:57,161
You're all torn up right now.

2426
01:16:57,531 --> 01:16:58,930
You're looking awful to say something cool right now.

2427
01:16:58,931 --> 01:16:59,960
That's his passion.

2428
01:16:59,961 --> 01:17:01,731
I'm fine. What is there to life?

2429
01:17:01,831 --> 01:17:03,330
- Tell me!
- Hold on.

2430
01:17:03,331 --> 01:17:04,900
You're a mess right now.

2431
01:17:04,901 --> 01:17:07,201
- Get yourself sorted.
- I'm fine.

2432
01:17:07,271 --> 01:17:09,510
- It looks a bit off.
- I can still look confident.

2433
01:17:09,511 --> 01:17:11,510
Hold on. It looks a bit off.

2434
01:17:11,511 --> 01:17:12,740
- Really? Does this look off?
- Yes.

2435
01:17:12,741 --> 01:17:14,181
Your agency won't like this.

2436
01:17:15,881 --> 01:17:18,150
All right, everyone. We'll start Round Two.

2437
01:17:18,151 --> 01:17:20,221
We'll start setting up for Round Two now.

2438
01:17:20,881 --> 01:17:22,720
- Isn't it jump rope?
- No. It isn't jump rope.

2439
01:17:22,721 --> 01:17:23,920
- No?
- Hold on.

2440
01:17:23,921 --> 01:17:25,360
- What? It's UFC.
- Is it a ring?

2441
01:17:25,361 --> 01:17:26,721
- Nice.
- Okay.

2442
01:17:26,921 --> 01:17:29,691
All right, everyone. This is the game for Round Two.

2443
01:17:30,091 --> 01:17:31,660
It's Circular Tug of War.

2444
01:17:31,661 --> 01:17:33,077
- What is that?
- Circular Tug of War?

2445
01:17:33,101 --> 01:17:35,070
- What is that?
- That will be used for Tug of War.

2446
01:17:35,071 --> 01:17:36,271
- How is this played?
- How?

2447
01:17:36,331 --> 01:17:38,470
The rope that is shaped as a circle will be pulled at the same time.

2448
01:17:38,471 --> 01:17:39,700
The first team to have...

2449
01:17:39,701 --> 01:17:42,410
all members to pull out their flags will win.

2450
01:17:42,411 --> 01:17:44,540
Am I not allowed to pull out all three flags?

2451
01:17:44,541 --> 01:17:46,440
- No. Just 1.
- It's 1 each?

2452
01:17:46,441 --> 01:17:48,161
- Only one flag can be pulled out.
- I see.

2453
01:17:48,351 --> 01:17:49,850
- We have to be smart as well.
- Right.

2454
01:17:49,851 --> 01:17:51,850
- It's not just about strength.
- Right. We have to be smart.

2455
01:17:51,851 --> 01:17:53,720
Even so, strength is required.

2456
01:17:53,721 --> 01:17:54,881
It's still good to be strong.

2457
01:17:55,021 --> 01:17:57,451
We can't deny the truth, can we?

2458
01:17:58,321 --> 01:17:59,990
- What do we do, then?
- What must we do?

2459
01:17:59,991 --> 01:18:02,831
We have to use our wisdom in the midst of this...

2460
01:18:03,091 --> 01:18:05,600
and find the best way to win.

2461
01:18:05,601 --> 01:18:07,230
- All right, everyone.
- Gather up.

2462
01:18:07,231 --> 01:18:08,931
Mike Tyson left a famous quote.

2463
01:18:09,071 --> 01:18:11,431
"Everyone has a plan until they get punched in the mouth."

2464
01:18:13,641 --> 01:18:15,911
- That's Mike Tyson's famous quote.
- Mike Tyson?

2465
01:18:16,471 --> 01:18:17,471
What a great quote.

2466
01:18:17,971 --> 01:18:20,541
With the way we see it,

2467
01:18:20,911 --> 01:18:24,411
Se Yoon will be like Seon Ho without using one arm.

2468
01:18:25,281 --> 01:18:27,021
What's the most harmful insect to human?

2469
01:18:27,381 --> 01:18:29,220
- It's Lack of Effort.
- That's not what this is about.

2470
01:18:29,221 --> 01:18:31,691
- Using one arm...
- I will never be lazy in my life.

2471
01:18:32,461 --> 01:18:33,990
I've been lazy enough throughout my life!

2472
01:18:33,991 --> 01:18:35,130
That's why...

2473
01:18:35,131 --> 01:18:37,591
That's why you have to be careful with what you say!

2474
01:18:38,261 --> 01:18:41,031
I will no longer be lazy after meeting Yunho.

2475
01:18:41,661 --> 01:18:43,370
- Let's just get this over with.
- Right.

2476
01:18:43,371 --> 01:18:44,400
I'll use one arm.

2477
01:18:44,401 --> 01:18:45,740
Okay!

2478
01:18:45,741 --> 01:18:47,421
- We'll take turns.
- Watch him carefully.

2479
01:18:47,941 --> 01:18:49,010
Sure.

2480
01:18:49,011 --> 01:18:51,071
You will get disqualified for using both arms!

2481
01:18:51,911 --> 01:18:54,141
What's with your eyes? I won't use one arm.

2482
01:18:54,541 --> 01:18:55,681
I'm sorry.

2483
01:18:55,811 --> 01:18:57,510
- Go down lower.
- Right.

2484
01:18:57,511 --> 01:18:59,081
(A big apology)

2485
01:18:59,281 --> 01:19:00,980
Get to your positions, everyone.

2486
01:19:00,981 --> 01:19:01,990
(His team members feel embarrassed.)

2487
01:19:01,991 --> 01:19:04,221
All right, Joon and Jae Jun.

2488
01:19:04,491 --> 01:19:06,260
We'll share our plan openly.

2489
01:19:06,261 --> 01:19:07,461
Who should get the flag first?

2490
01:19:08,161 --> 01:19:09,830
- I'll get my flag first.
- Sure.

2491
01:19:09,831 --> 01:19:10,890
It'll be me first.

2492
01:19:10,891 --> 01:19:12,430
Jae Jun will be second. Joon will be the last one.

2493
01:19:12,431 --> 01:19:14,301
- Right.
- Let's get this done neatly.

2494
01:19:14,501 --> 01:19:16,300
- Okay.
- What will you do, Yunho?

2495
01:19:16,301 --> 01:19:17,607
(Team Jae Jun will keep it simple and use their strength.)

2496
01:19:17,631 --> 01:19:19,701
- We'll pull together at the start.
- Right.

2497
01:19:19,841 --> 01:19:21,370
- When they head somewhere, - Right.

2498
01:19:21,371 --> 01:19:23,270
We'll run toward that side at the count of three.

2499
01:19:23,271 --> 01:19:24,311
Okay.

2500
01:19:24,741 --> 01:19:27,810
After a great hit, your face will be in the air.

2501
01:19:27,811 --> 01:19:30,180
When you come back down, I will stamp you on the ground.

2502
01:19:30,181 --> 01:19:33,120
I will make you get discovered next summer with the clams.

2503
01:19:33,121 --> 01:19:34,351
- Okay.
- Okay.

2504
01:19:34,521 --> 01:19:35,991
Okay. We'll begin!

2505
01:19:36,151 --> 01:19:37,220
- What were we going to do?
- Get ready!

2506
01:19:37,221 --> 01:19:38,290
No grabbing.

2507
01:19:38,291 --> 01:19:39,321
Do we all get up?

2508
01:19:39,491 --> 01:19:41,121
Start pulling right away.

2509
01:19:44,391 --> 01:19:45,461
Two, three!

2510
01:19:46,631 --> 01:19:49,230
(Team Jae Jun heads toward Se Yoon's flag as mentioned.)

2511
01:19:49,231 --> 01:19:50,231
Let's go!

2512
01:19:51,701 --> 01:19:54,401
(They begin with their plan.)

2513
01:19:54,771 --> 01:19:57,241
(Shaking up the balance by using their strength)

2514
01:19:57,411 --> 01:19:58,810
(Swaying)

2515
01:19:58,811 --> 01:19:59,840
Take out the flag!

2516
01:19:59,841 --> 01:20:01,310
- Go!
- Jong Min!

2517
01:20:01,311 --> 01:20:03,511
Come this way, Jong Min!

2518
01:20:04,881 --> 01:20:06,720
- Take out the flag!
- Take out the flag!

2519
01:20:06,721 --> 01:20:08,121
(Team Jae Jun gets one flag first.)

2520
01:20:08,251 --> 01:20:10,391
Come this way, Jong Min!

2521
01:20:10,551 --> 01:20:11,551
This way!

2522
01:20:11,651 --> 01:20:13,660
Get the flag, Yunho! Done!

2523
01:20:13,661 --> 01:20:15,090
(Yunho takes out the flag at that moment.)

2524
01:20:15,091 --> 01:20:16,831
- Okay!
- Where do we go now?

2525
01:20:17,291 --> 01:20:18,660
- Move back!
- Move back!

2526
01:20:18,661 --> 01:20:19,761
This way!

2527
01:20:19,861 --> 01:20:22,231
(Current situation)

2528
01:20:22,571 --> 01:20:24,631
- Move back!
- This way!

2529
01:20:25,241 --> 01:20:27,500
(Team Jae Jun gets the 2nd flag.)

2530
01:20:27,501 --> 01:20:29,621
- Hey, Joon! It's yours now.
- We have to get Joon's.

2531
01:20:30,071 --> 01:20:32,641
(Team Jae Jun will win if they get Joon's flag.)

2532
01:20:33,141 --> 01:20:34,211
Gosh!

2533
01:20:34,341 --> 01:20:35,450
(Joon is on the ground.)

2534
01:20:35,451 --> 01:20:37,081
Hey, Joon! It's yours now.

2535
01:20:37,511 --> 01:20:38,981
- You have to go.
- No!

2536
01:20:40,551 --> 01:20:41,991
Joon! There you go.

2537
01:20:42,421 --> 01:20:44,791
(The game will end if he gets the flag.)

2538
01:20:44,891 --> 01:20:45,920
Help me!

2539
01:20:45,921 --> 01:20:47,461
(Will he make it?)

2540
01:20:47,561 --> 01:20:48,591
Help me!

2541
01:20:48,831 --> 01:20:51,361
(Is he getting pulled back?)

2542
01:20:51,631 --> 01:20:52,930
Move back!

2543
01:20:52,931 --> 01:20:54,261
- Move back!
- Move back!

2544
01:20:54,501 --> 01:20:57,371
(Team Yunho moves to the opposite direction.)

2545
01:20:57,601 --> 01:21:00,001
(Joon fails to get his flag due to Team Yunho's strategy.)

2546
01:21:00,201 --> 01:21:02,841
- We have to go, DinDin.
- Go, DinDin!

2547
01:21:03,241 --> 01:21:06,041
(Team Yunho helps DinDin get his flag.)

2548
01:21:06,211 --> 01:21:08,781
- I got it!
- Nice.

2549
01:21:09,251 --> 01:21:11,311
(What about Joon?)

2550
01:21:12,051 --> 01:21:15,490
(He's getting dragged again.)

2551
01:21:15,491 --> 01:21:16,591
Push me!

2552
01:21:16,651 --> 01:21:19,261
- Jong Min!
- Jong Min!

2553
01:21:19,621 --> 01:21:23,731
(The first to get the final flag will take the win.)

2554
01:21:23,931 --> 01:21:27,461
(There's a great battle of strength for the final flag.)

2555
01:21:28,871 --> 01:21:32,670
(Se Yoon falls to the ground as well.)

2556
01:21:32,671 --> 01:21:34,200
- Go!
- Pull!

2557
01:21:34,201 --> 01:21:36,511
- I can't move!
- Go! We can do it!

2558
01:21:36,911 --> 01:21:38,711
- We can do it!
- Come on!

2559
01:21:39,011 --> 01:21:41,880
(Jong Min gets closer to the final flag.)

2560
01:21:41,881 --> 01:21:43,150
- Get it!
- Get down!

2561
01:21:43,151 --> 01:21:45,280
- Get down!
- Get down!

2562
01:21:45,281 --> 01:21:47,520
- Take it!
- We won!

2563
01:21:47,521 --> 01:21:49,591
(Team Yunho wins Round 2.)

2564
01:21:49,851 --> 01:21:51,020
That was a great strategy.

2565
01:21:51,021 --> 01:21:52,561
It's over once you fall to the ground.

2566
01:21:53,191 --> 01:21:54,560
He fell to the ground.

2567
01:21:54,561 --> 01:21:56,330
- He fell to the ground.
- He fell to the ground.

2568
01:21:56,331 --> 01:21:58,461
Gosh, I'm dying!

2569
01:21:59,101 --> 01:22:00,630
That was great.

2570
01:22:00,631 --> 01:22:01,830
(They're tied now.)

2571
01:22:01,831 --> 01:22:03,531
- I feel the passion.
- We won.

2572
01:22:03,671 --> 01:22:06,500
Gosh, the glove got torn open.

2573
01:22:06,501 --> 01:22:08,640
- Check out his passion!
- Check out his passion!

2574
01:22:08,641 --> 01:22:10,440
- His glove got torn open.
- Why?

2575
01:22:10,441 --> 01:22:12,217
- His glove got torn open.
- Tear open yours as well.

2576
01:22:12,241 --> 01:22:13,440
Why do that?

2577
01:22:13,441 --> 01:22:14,640
(Fabricated passion)

2578
01:22:14,641 --> 01:22:16,381
We want compliments as well. Gosh.

2579
01:22:17,381 --> 01:22:19,921
The score is 1 to 1 right now.

2580
01:22:20,551 --> 01:22:22,491
This is the final round.

2581
01:22:22,851 --> 01:22:24,490
This one is called Loyalty Relay.

2582
01:22:24,491 --> 01:22:25,991
(Loyalty Relay)

2583
01:22:26,261 --> 01:22:29,091
(Team Yunho is confident in running.)

2584
01:22:29,561 --> 01:22:31,891
We don't stand a chance. You should run the whole race.

2585
01:22:32,301 --> 01:22:33,900
- What?
- Hey!

2586
01:22:33,901 --> 01:22:35,331
Come on, Jae Jun.

2587
01:22:35,571 --> 01:22:37,831
That can't happen. It's a game of loyalty.

2588
01:22:38,331 --> 01:22:40,301
The baton will be passed to you in advance.

2589
01:22:40,371 --> 01:22:42,171
- Gosh.
- Please pass the baton.

2590
01:22:42,411 --> 01:22:44,111
- Gosh!
- Gosh!

2591
01:22:44,241 --> 01:22:45,511
That changes things.

2592
01:22:45,811 --> 01:22:47,140
So that will be used as the baton.

2593
01:22:47,141 --> 01:22:48,981
- Yunho is really fast.
- We'll be using this?

2594
01:22:49,381 --> 01:22:51,251
(A parasol baton)

2595
01:22:52,351 --> 01:22:55,180
You will run a 100m race holding this.

2596
01:22:55,181 --> 01:22:57,491
(A 100m relay)

2597
01:22:57,591 --> 01:22:58,890
- Run with this?
- Try holding it.

2598
01:22:58,891 --> 01:23:00,190
Hold it and see how it feels.

2599
01:23:00,191 --> 01:23:02,130
- It's the wind.
- This is heavy.

2600
01:23:02,131 --> 01:23:04,630
- You should run like this.
- I see.

2601
01:23:04,631 --> 01:23:06,360
You're right. You need to be strong.

2602
01:23:06,361 --> 01:23:07,760
- Try holding it.
- This is...

2603
01:23:07,761 --> 01:23:09,170
I can do this.

2604
01:23:09,171 --> 01:23:10,677
(Being simply fast isn't an advantage.)

2605
01:23:10,701 --> 01:23:12,241
How are we going to hold this?

2606
01:23:12,471 --> 01:23:13,900
This is the right way.

2607
01:23:13,901 --> 01:23:15,021
You can't hold it like this.

2608
01:23:15,571 --> 01:23:17,671
We just can't run holding it like this.

2609
01:23:18,141 --> 01:23:19,411
Let's do this.

2610
01:23:20,181 --> 01:23:22,881
So, this is what you want.

2611
01:23:24,211 --> 01:23:25,251
What?

2612
01:23:27,451 --> 01:23:30,021
(Where is he going?)

2613
01:23:30,421 --> 01:23:31,451
What's wrong with him?

2614
01:23:32,361 --> 01:23:33,690
I'm supposed to run like this, but...

2615
01:23:33,691 --> 01:23:35,061
It's not easy.

2616
01:23:35,791 --> 01:23:37,090
(His mouth is sticking out with his shining front teeth.)

2617
01:23:37,091 --> 01:23:38,901
- He can't even walk forward.
- All right.

2618
01:23:39,061 --> 01:23:40,730
(Yunho steps up.)

2619
01:23:40,731 --> 01:23:42,070
I get it now.

2620
01:23:42,071 --> 01:23:43,830
His mouth is sticking out.

2621
01:23:43,831 --> 01:23:45,370
- I just...
- I'll do it.

2622
01:23:45,371 --> 01:23:47,440
- You're right.
- I need to run a short distance.

2623
01:23:47,441 --> 01:23:49,471
He almost got upset with the parasol.

2624
01:23:49,771 --> 01:23:52,257
- I'm pushed back by the wind.
- Is it slapstick comedy or what?

2625
01:23:52,281 --> 01:23:54,080
That's the essence of this game!

2626
01:23:54,081 --> 01:23:55,081
- Right.
- Like this?

2627
01:23:55,082 --> 01:23:56,650
- This is what we're supposed to do.
- What's the point of playing it...

2628
01:23:56,651 --> 01:23:58,381
- if we hold it like this?
- Okay.

2629
01:23:58,551 --> 01:24:00,620
- This is ridiculous.
- We will do that.

2630
01:24:00,621 --> 01:24:02,321
- Okay.
- It's getting hot.

2631
01:24:02,521 --> 01:24:03,620
- Okay. Let's go.
- All right.

2632
01:24:03,621 --> 01:24:05,291
- Let's go.
- All right, then.

2633
01:24:05,491 --> 01:24:06,760
Now, you can have a strategy meeting...

2634
01:24:06,761 --> 01:24:08,681
- and divide the sections.
- Just give up on me.

2635
01:24:09,061 --> 01:24:11,031
The weight is what matters.

2636
01:24:11,761 --> 01:24:12,861
What did you say?

2637
01:24:13,161 --> 01:24:14,731
Weight... What?

2638
01:24:15,431 --> 01:24:17,231
Did I see you wrong in the movie, "Luck-Key?"

2639
01:24:17,471 --> 01:24:20,041
- Maybe we need subtitles.
- What did you say?

2640
01:24:20,301 --> 01:24:21,540
It's about weight.

2641
01:24:21,541 --> 01:24:23,441
- It's not about speed.
- Hang on.

2642
01:24:23,671 --> 01:24:25,740
We should use our weight.

2643
01:24:25,741 --> 01:24:27,280
This isn't about running.

2644
01:24:27,281 --> 01:24:28,380
We're going to win.

2645
01:24:28,381 --> 01:24:29,510
Just run 10m then.

2646
01:24:29,511 --> 01:24:31,580
- Okay. I can do that.
- Just run 10m.

2647
01:24:31,581 --> 01:24:32,721
We'll run 40m and 50m.

2648
01:24:32,881 --> 01:24:34,681
- We must win.
- Right.

2649
01:24:35,491 --> 01:24:39,020
I think the probability of us winning this is very high.

2650
01:24:39,021 --> 01:24:40,290
If we lose...

2651
01:24:40,291 --> 01:24:41,291
(On the other hand, Team Yunho is worried.)

2652
01:24:41,292 --> 01:24:42,861
They run fast and are strong.

2653
01:24:43,431 --> 01:24:44,431
Look.

2654
01:24:44,631 --> 01:24:46,561
So it's from here to here.

2655
01:24:46,961 --> 01:24:48,360
I'll start.

2656
01:24:48,361 --> 01:24:50,170
- Okay.
- How far are you going to run?

2657
01:24:50,171 --> 01:24:51,331
- About 20m?
- I'll run 10m.

2658
01:24:51,601 --> 01:24:52,601
Only 10m?

2659
01:24:52,602 --> 01:24:53,640
(You're only running that much?)

2660
01:24:53,641 --> 01:24:56,010
And you'll take the parasol and run 10m.

2661
01:24:56,011 --> 01:24:57,740
(Start, finish)

2662
01:24:57,741 --> 01:24:59,381
Then, Yunho will run the rest.

2663
01:25:01,311 --> 01:25:02,311
He will run 80m?

2664
01:25:03,311 --> 01:25:05,920
You have passion and mental strength, after all.

2665
01:25:05,921 --> 01:25:06,981
Of course.

2666
01:25:07,351 --> 01:25:09,020
I'm just going to keep charging.

2667
01:25:09,021 --> 01:25:10,950
- For the win.
- Okay.

2668
01:25:10,951 --> 01:25:13,090
I'll just take the parasol and run straight ahead.

2669
01:25:13,091 --> 01:25:14,721
All right, everyone.

2670
01:25:14,821 --> 01:25:16,430
- Are you done with the strategy?
- Yes.

2671
01:25:16,431 --> 01:25:18,730
- Let's go to the starting point.
- Go to your positions, then.

2672
01:25:18,731 --> 01:25:19,931
- Let's go.
- All right.

2673
01:25:20,561 --> 01:25:21,960
Around here. How about it?

2674
01:25:21,961 --> 01:25:24,130
- I'll take the parasol here.
- Okay.

2675
01:25:24,131 --> 01:25:26,340
While I run, you should come this way and take it.

2676
01:25:26,341 --> 01:25:27,901
- All right.
- Do you know what I mean?

2677
01:25:28,071 --> 01:25:29,840
I wish the wind would blow a lot.

2678
01:25:29,841 --> 01:25:31,487
(Team Jae Jun pushes forward with power rather than speed.)

2679
01:25:31,511 --> 01:25:33,111
Please, let the wind blow.

2680
01:25:33,941 --> 01:25:36,281
- All right. Let's do this.
- Let's go!

2681
01:25:37,151 --> 01:25:40,480
(For Team Yunho, Yunho has to run 80m all by himself.)

2682
01:25:40,481 --> 01:25:44,621
(For Team Jae Jun, Jae Jun and Joon run similar distances.)

2683
01:25:45,091 --> 01:25:46,790
This is no big deal, but I'm still feeling nervous.

2684
01:25:46,791 --> 01:25:48,497
(Which team will cross the finish line first?)

2685
01:25:48,521 --> 01:25:50,831
- Let's begin.
- Right away?

2686
01:25:51,931 --> 01:25:54,460
(A dive into the water...)

2687
01:25:54,461 --> 01:25:57,201
(is at stake in this race.)

2688
01:25:57,431 --> 01:25:58,431
Let's do this!

2689
01:25:59,701 --> 01:26:01,641
(Determined)

2690
01:26:02,001 --> 01:26:04,111
(The last game with a dive at stake)

2691
01:26:04,271 --> 01:26:07,441
(Parasol Loyalty Relay)

2692
01:26:08,341 --> 01:26:10,181
(Two people are running out at the same time.)

2693
01:26:11,381 --> 01:26:12,520
(A fierce wind is blowing as soon as it starts.)

2694
01:26:12,521 --> 01:26:16,051
(Flapping)

2695
01:26:16,851 --> 01:26:18,991
(The paper doll is unable to move forward.)

2696
01:26:19,321 --> 01:26:21,191
(Struggling)

2697
01:26:21,921 --> 01:26:23,667
(Even so, he doesn't forget to keep an eye on the other team.)

2698
01:26:23,691 --> 01:26:25,631
(Anxious)

2699
01:26:26,401 --> 01:26:28,631
(A headwind is blowing toward Se Yoon as well.)

2700
01:26:29,001 --> 01:26:31,301
(Se Yoon overcomes the wind with his strength.)

2701
01:26:31,871 --> 01:26:32,901
Go.

2702
01:26:32,941 --> 01:26:34,841
(Team Jae Jun hands over the baton.)

2703
01:26:35,911 --> 01:26:37,541
(The parasol is turned inside out!)

2704
01:26:37,771 --> 01:26:39,180
(Jae Jun overcomes the wind with his sheer strength.)

2705
01:26:39,181 --> 01:26:41,111
Go! Let's go!

2706
01:26:41,511 --> 01:26:42,680
Take this.

2707
01:26:42,681 --> 01:26:44,487
(Just then, Team Yunho hands over the baton too.)

2708
01:26:44,511 --> 01:26:46,251
(The 2nd runner of Team Yunho, Jong Min)

2709
01:26:46,751 --> 01:26:47,980
(Jong Min is also outmatched in strength.)

2710
01:26:47,981 --> 01:26:50,151
(Running in place)

2711
01:26:50,491 --> 01:26:52,521
Go. Hurry, Jae Jun.

2712
01:26:53,291 --> 01:26:55,851
(Team Jae Jun is pulling ahead thanks to the fatties' strength.)

2713
01:26:56,131 --> 01:26:58,691
(The baton is passed to Yunho while falling behind.)

2714
01:26:59,201 --> 01:27:01,431
(Meanwhile, the gap widens.)

2715
01:27:01,601 --> 01:27:03,370
(Yunho steps up.)

2716
01:27:03,371 --> 01:27:06,201
- U-Know Yunho, passion!
- Faster!

2717
01:27:09,841 --> 01:27:12,281
(I, Jung Yunho, am a man who is nothing without his passion.)

2718
01:27:14,011 --> 01:27:16,151
- It's neck and neck.
- We don't know it yet.

2719
01:27:16,551 --> 01:27:18,911
(The last runner of Team Jae Jun)

2720
01:27:19,781 --> 01:27:20,850
Hurry. Go.

2721
01:27:20,851 --> 01:27:22,751
(A head-to-head showdown between the aces)

2722
01:27:23,491 --> 01:27:24,521
(Stumbling)

2723
01:27:24,591 --> 01:27:26,421
(Joon slips for a moment.)

2724
01:27:26,891 --> 01:27:28,921
(Yunho pushes ahead while Joon stumbles.)

2725
01:27:29,061 --> 01:27:30,391
(We can't go into the water.)

2726
01:27:30,691 --> 01:27:32,301
(Desperate)

2727
01:27:32,631 --> 01:27:34,461
(Who will cross the finish line first?)

2728
01:27:35,261 --> 01:27:41,501
(Yunho arrives first!)

2729
01:27:41,541 --> 01:27:42,541
Passion!

2730
01:27:43,011 --> 01:27:44,011
What?

2731
01:27:44,471 --> 01:27:45,840
(His passion is crazy!)

2732
01:27:45,841 --> 01:27:47,941
- You did it!
- Passion!

2733
01:27:48,441 --> 01:27:51,451
(A dramatic reversal created by passion)

2734
01:27:51,611 --> 01:27:53,420
(Team Yunho wins the Dive Game.)

2735
01:27:53,421 --> 01:27:54,881
He ran most of the race.

2736
01:27:55,021 --> 01:27:56,790
Congratulations, Yunho!

2737
01:27:56,791 --> 01:27:58,290
Congratulations, Yunho!

2738
01:27:58,291 --> 01:27:59,561
Thanks!

2739
01:28:01,061 --> 01:28:03,090
(It's confirmed...)

2740
01:28:03,091 --> 01:28:05,461
(that they're getting into the water.)

2741
01:28:05,801 --> 01:28:07,360
- The energy...
- He did a great job.

2742
01:28:07,361 --> 01:28:09,130
We ended up getting caught up.

2743
01:28:09,131 --> 01:28:10,871
We will get into the water!

2744
01:28:11,101 --> 01:28:12,101
But, just in case...

2745
01:28:12,871 --> 01:28:14,771
(Just in case?)

2746
01:28:14,801 --> 01:28:16,810
I'd like to ask one person.

2747
01:28:16,811 --> 01:28:17,871
What?

2748
01:28:19,241 --> 01:28:20,481
- By any chance...
- All right.

2749
01:28:20,981 --> 01:28:23,081
- By any chance?
- With passion?

2750
01:28:23,151 --> 01:28:24,981
- With your passion...
- Just in case.

2751
01:28:25,881 --> 01:28:26,881
Are you going to dive?

2752
01:28:27,451 --> 01:28:28,921
- Do you want it?
- Yes.

2753
01:28:29,921 --> 01:28:31,450
- Seriously?
- Will you do it if I want?

2754
01:28:31,451 --> 01:28:32,520
Unbelievable.

2755
01:28:32,521 --> 01:28:34,760
- Three important things in life.
- Yunho.

2756
01:28:34,761 --> 01:28:37,160
- Gold, salt, and now.
- Now.

2757
01:28:37,161 --> 01:28:38,931
- Now.
- Now.

2758
01:28:39,031 --> 01:28:40,200
- Seriously?
- No way.

2759
01:28:40,201 --> 01:28:41,761
There is salt in the sea.

2760
01:28:41,831 --> 01:28:43,571
- Do you want it?
- Yes.

2761
01:28:44,001 --> 01:28:45,271
- Do you want it?
- Yes.

2762
01:28:45,741 --> 01:28:46,940
- Do you want it?
- I do.

2763
01:28:46,941 --> 01:28:48,201
- Do you want it?
- Yes.

2764
01:28:49,001 --> 01:28:50,141
Let's go, then!

2765
01:28:51,371 --> 01:28:52,940
(He declares that he'll voluntarily enter the water.)

2766
01:28:52,941 --> 01:28:54,111
U-Know Yunho!

2767
01:28:54,511 --> 01:28:57,251
(An explosive reaction)

2768
01:28:57,481 --> 01:28:58,910
- Let's go!
- It's happening.

2769
01:28:58,911 --> 01:29:01,151
- He's really doing it.
- I'm scared.

2770
01:29:01,481 --> 01:29:03,951
Hey, you ran 80m just not to enter the water.

2771
01:29:04,291 --> 01:29:07,121
Let's hurry and get ready before the sweat cools down.

2772
01:29:07,161 --> 01:29:08,491
It's so funny.

2773
01:29:09,061 --> 01:29:10,461
Yunho is the best.

2774
01:29:10,691 --> 01:29:11,760
Thanks, Yunho.

2775
01:29:11,761 --> 01:29:13,360
You're doing all this for today.

2776
01:29:13,361 --> 01:29:14,431
Seriously.

2777
01:29:14,901 --> 01:29:17,701
This is why what you say...

2778
01:29:17,971 --> 01:29:19,471
is important.

2779
01:29:20,341 --> 01:29:22,622
It is good to think about what you say from time to time.

2780
01:29:23,071 --> 01:29:25,311
Actually, we can join them and enter the water, too.

2781
01:29:25,371 --> 01:29:26,680
- But we can't all do that.
- You're right.

2782
01:29:26,681 --> 01:29:28,817
- I mean, we played games for this.
- What's the point of playing games?

2783
01:29:28,841 --> 01:29:30,910
- The weather is warm.
- Anyone can enter the water.

2784
01:29:30,911 --> 01:29:32,880
- I really want to enter the water.
- If it were cold, I'd understand.

2785
01:29:32,881 --> 01:29:35,051
- It was cold earlier.
- It is warm now.

2786
01:29:35,421 --> 01:29:37,921
(Se Yoon helps his friend prepare to enter the water.)

2787
01:29:38,421 --> 01:29:40,021
- Oh, dear.
- It's not bad.

2788
01:29:41,721 --> 01:29:42,761
It's very bad.

2789
01:29:43,391 --> 01:29:45,331
How does he do a somersault with that body?

2790
01:29:45,461 --> 01:29:46,600
That's amazing.

2791
01:29:46,601 --> 01:29:48,960
- This is Yunho's first time here.
- Let's dive in!

2792
01:29:48,961 --> 01:29:50,071
(Ready to enter the water)

2793
01:29:50,601 --> 01:29:52,771
Spring has not come to the sea yet.

2794
01:29:53,141 --> 01:29:55,041
All right, U-Know Yunho.

2795
01:29:55,201 --> 01:29:57,510
Say something cool before you enter the water.

2796
01:29:57,511 --> 01:29:58,811
All right. Today...

2797
01:29:59,381 --> 01:30:02,080
The number 26 sounds like take-off in the Korean language.

2798
01:30:02,081 --> 01:30:03,380
That's right. Take-off.

2799
01:30:03,381 --> 01:30:04,381
(Impressed)

2800
01:30:04,382 --> 01:30:05,550
He's a quote-making machine.

2801
01:30:05,551 --> 01:30:06,680
He really is.

2802
01:30:06,681 --> 01:30:09,620
We will hope for 2 Days 1 Night's magnificent take-off in 2026.

2803
01:30:09,621 --> 01:30:10,750
- That sounds great.
- Nice.

2804
01:30:10,751 --> 01:30:12,420
I'll say, "To a new take-off for 2 Days 1 Night!"

2805
01:30:12,421 --> 01:30:14,290
- And you'll say, "Take-off!"
- Okay.

2806
01:30:14,291 --> 01:30:15,491
- All right.
- That's so cool.

2807
01:30:15,691 --> 01:30:16,890
Yunho, you're really cool.

2808
01:30:16,891 --> 01:30:18,760
You should say it with us.

2809
01:30:18,761 --> 01:30:20,331
- Of course.
- Let's do this.

2810
01:30:21,001 --> 01:30:24,030
To a new take-off for 2 Days 1 Night!

2811
01:30:24,031 --> 01:30:26,100
- Okay! Take-off!
- Take-off!

2812
01:30:26,101 --> 01:30:27,471
- Take-off!
- Take-off!

2813
01:30:28,071 --> 01:30:30,740
(They take off powerfully.)

2814
01:30:30,741 --> 01:30:32,441
(He runs away as soon as it begins.)

2815
01:30:32,741 --> 01:30:35,011
(The runaway is apprehended right away.)

2816
01:30:35,581 --> 01:30:38,711
(Entering the water all together)

2817
01:30:39,551 --> 01:30:43,021
(Splash)

2818
01:30:43,691 --> 01:30:48,921
(Charging into the sea with spirit)

2819
01:30:49,491 --> 01:30:51,731
(But the sea in March is still cold.)

2820
01:30:52,131 --> 01:30:54,061
(It must be cold.)

2821
01:30:54,131 --> 01:30:56,371
Three seconds!

2822
01:30:56,571 --> 01:30:58,671
(The reason they keep shouting 3 seconds)

2823
01:30:58,771 --> 01:31:00,270
Wait three seconds,

2824
01:31:00,271 --> 01:31:01,877
- and you'll get used to it!
- Three seconds!

2825
01:31:01,901 --> 01:31:03,110
Come here.

2826
01:31:03,111 --> 01:31:06,711
(To see if it's true, they submerge up to the top of their heads.)

2827
01:31:06,911 --> 01:31:09,111
(Interesting)

2828
01:31:09,381 --> 01:31:11,711
(Are Yunho's words true?)

2829
01:31:13,721 --> 01:31:14,781
It's cold!

2830
01:31:15,081 --> 01:31:17,691
(It's still cold even after 3 seconds.)

2831
01:31:18,591 --> 01:31:19,591
(Screaming)

2832
01:31:19,821 --> 01:31:20,990
It's cold!

2833
01:31:20,991 --> 01:31:22,791
What's with them?

2834
01:31:23,031 --> 01:31:24,060
(It looks like this from the outside.)

2835
01:31:24,061 --> 01:31:25,961
(Peaceful, chaotic)

2836
01:31:26,631 --> 01:31:30,601
(A new take-off for the year 2026)

2837
01:31:31,201 --> 01:31:33,071
2 Days 1 Night!

2838
01:31:33,171 --> 01:31:36,141
I think what Yunho has is not passion but manic symptoms.

2839
01:31:36,211 --> 01:31:37,241
I'm serious.

2840
01:31:37,871 --> 01:31:39,281
He's insane.

2841
01:31:40,511 --> 01:31:41,580
Hurry and come here.

2842
01:31:41,581 --> 01:31:45,081
(Passionate Man's extraordinary dive)

2843
01:31:45,211 --> 01:31:46,480
- Hurry and get out.
- Hurry.

2844
01:31:46,481 --> 01:31:48,520
Good work, everyone.

2845
01:31:48,521 --> 01:31:50,050
(Everyone hurriedly gets out except Yunho.)

2846
01:31:50,051 --> 01:31:51,221
Is it cold?

2847
01:31:51,421 --> 01:31:52,861
It's really cold.

2848
01:31:53,361 --> 01:31:54,391
Is it cold?

2849
01:31:55,091 --> 01:31:56,131
Are you all right?

2850
01:31:56,691 --> 01:31:58,790
- Yunho is strange.
- U-Know Yunho!

2851
01:31:58,791 --> 01:32:00,131
U-Know Yunho is weird.

2852
01:32:00,801 --> 01:32:02,260
(His passion doesn't die down even after entering the water.)

2853
01:32:02,261 --> 01:32:03,531
Passion!

2854
01:32:04,301 --> 01:32:06,171
- Seriously...
- I realized this after a dive.

2855
01:32:06,601 --> 01:32:09,141
It takes about 5 seconds, not 3, to get used to it.

2856
01:32:09,271 --> 01:32:11,210
Actually, after three seconds,

2857
01:32:11,211 --> 01:32:12,841
it got much colder rapidly.

2858
01:32:13,141 --> 01:32:14,440
- I'm serious.
- I know, right?

2859
01:32:14,441 --> 01:32:16,350
Let's go and get changed.

2860
01:32:16,351 --> 01:32:18,451
- Thank you, everyone.
- All right.

2861
01:32:18,911 --> 01:32:21,151
- That was unbelievable.
- Was it cold?

2862
01:32:21,351 --> 01:32:23,321
- The water is like ice.
- Is it?

2863
01:32:23,591 --> 01:32:25,821
It was like the Hwacheon Sancheoneo Ice Festival.

2864
01:32:26,091 --> 01:32:27,497
- It was freezing.
- It's still cold.

2865
01:32:27,521 --> 01:32:28,720
- Is it cold?
- It's really cold.

2866
01:32:28,721 --> 01:32:30,801
If Yunho finds it cold, that means it's really cold.

2867
01:32:31,091 --> 01:32:33,300
Did it feel warmer after five seconds?

2868
01:32:33,301 --> 01:32:35,231
- It gets colder.
- It's a lot colder.

2869
01:32:35,531 --> 01:32:37,370
Reason and emotion fought for a moment.

2870
01:32:37,371 --> 01:32:38,747
(Reason and emotion fought after 5 seconds.)

2871
01:32:38,771 --> 01:32:41,341
(The 2026 Passionate Dive is complete.)

2872
01:32:41,471 --> 01:32:43,241
(Next episode)

2873
01:32:43,711 --> 01:32:48,281
(The passionate time is not over yet.)

2874
01:32:48,981 --> 01:32:50,050
(Failure?)

2875
01:32:50,051 --> 01:32:52,011
(What is that even?)

2876
01:32:52,681 --> 01:32:54,880
(Is this...)

2877
01:32:54,881 --> 01:32:56,721
(the U-Know Yunho effect?)

2878
01:32:57,091 --> 01:32:59,251
(Smirking)

2879
01:33:00,861 --> 01:33:03,761
(However, a dark shadow comes upon them.)

2880
01:33:04,431 --> 01:33:07,361
(Six men in crisis)

2881
01:33:08,001 --> 01:33:11,401
(Will the engine of passion shut down?)

2882
01:33:13,341 --> 01:33:16,071
(A siren goes off in the middle of the night.)

2883
01:33:17,211 --> 01:33:19,481
(Dozens of mysterious cars)

2884
01:33:19,781 --> 01:33:22,011
(Someone is watching you.)

2885
01:33:22,851 --> 01:33:25,111
(Get snapped and it's game over.)

2886
01:33:25,651 --> 01:33:28,081
(Their captors are closing in on them.)

2887
01:33:28,451 --> 01:33:31,891
(What fate will befall them?)

2888
01:33:33,321 --> 01:33:37,291
(See you next week.)
